(1, 1, 'Lay\'s Potato Chips India\'s Masala Magic', 'Lay\'s', 10, 'HIGH', '1_c78f69a4c49944288f7d891e9d2db83f.jpg', 'cks/?srsltid=AfmBOoraM-m519\nYouTube\nMaps\npullamsettymaanas...\nTotal Sugars\n2.5g\nAdded Sugars\n0.2g\n0%\nTotal Fat\n33.1 g\n10%\nSaturated Fat\n12.5 g\n11%\nTrans Fat\n0.1 g\n1%\nSodium\n993 mg\n10%\nApproximate\nop\ntatoes\nLay\'s\nelected\ners and\ntheir\ntaste\nure.\nLay\'s is the Registered Trade Mark of PepsiCo, Inc.\nINGREDIENTS: Potato, Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein,\nRice Bran Oil), \"Seasoning (\"Spices & Condiments,\nlodised Salt, Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical\nFlavouring Substances), Black Salt, Sugar, Tomato\nPowder, Maltodextrin, Acidity Regulators (330, 296, 334),\nAnticaking Agent (551), Colour (160c)).\n\"As flavouring agent. \"Contains Onion and Garlic\nALLERGEN ADVICE: Contains Barley\nPROPRIETARY FOOD - POTATO CHIPS (15.1)\nAs compared to previous Lay\'s India\'s\nMagic Masala packs. Limited period offer,\nvalid in select geographies.\nNERING\nWITH\n\'For details on PepsiCo\npartnership with farmers,\nvicit ununu naneicoindia on in\nLay\'s Potato Chips 48 grams (40 grams + 8 grams EXTRA) India\'s Masala Magic Fla\nE\nnute.com/images/detailed/4192/71p2u3-szxl.jpg', '{\"overall_score\": 10, \"risk_level\": \"HIGH\", \"overview\": \"This product explicitly contains barley, which is a gluten-containing grain. For an adult with gluten sensitivity, this makes the product entirely unsuitable and should be strictly avoided. Additionally, its highly processed nature, high fat, and sodium content are not ideal for overall health or hormonal balance.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Low (2.5g per serving)\", \"additives_count\": 7, \"allergens_found\": [\"Gluten\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Potato\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A whole food, naturally gluten-free, and generally safe for adults.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Rice Bran Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High in total and saturated fats (Palmolein), which can contribute to inflammation and may negatively impact hormonal balance if consumed excessively. This product contains 33.1g total fat and 12.5g saturated fat per serving.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While generally safe, the \'ALLERGEN ADVICE: Contains Barley\' suggests gluten-containing ingredients might be present within this broad category, making it a direct concern for gluten sensitivity.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Contributes significantly to the high sodium content (993 mg per serving), which is generally not recommended for regular consumption and can impact overall health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical Flavouring Substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"\'Natural flavourings\' can sometimes be derived from gluten-containing grains (like barley malt) and are often proprietary, making their exact composition unclear. This poses a potential hidden gluten risk for sensitive individuals, especially given the explicit barley warning.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Black Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Also contributes to the overall high sodium content (993 mg per serving), which should be consumed in moderation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While the amount of added sugar is low (0.2g), regular intake of even small amounts of added sugars contributes to overall sugar consumption, which can impact blood sugar regulation and potentially affect hormonal balance over time.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tomato Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A naturally derived ingredient, generally safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Maltodextrin\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Can be derived from wheat, although often processed to be gluten-free. Given the explicit \'Contains Barley\' warning, it raises additional concern about potential gluten cross-contamination or hidden gluten sources within the product for a gluten-sensitive individual.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulators (Citric Acid (330), Malic Acid (296), Tartaric Acid (334))\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Common food additives generally recognized as safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Anticaking Agent (Silicon Dioxide (551))\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common food additive generally recognized as safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Colour (Paprika Extract (160c))\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural food colorant derived from paprika, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Barley (as per allergen advice)\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"Barley contains gluten, which is a direct allergen for the user with gluten sensitivity. Its explicit presence makes this product entirely unsuitable and potentially harmful for consumption.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Allergen Risk (Gluten)\", \"description\": \"The explicit mention \'Contains Barley\' is a critical alert for this user. Barley is a gluten-containing grain, making this product highly unsuitable and dangerous for anyone with gluten sensitivity or celiac disease. Consumption could trigger significant adverse reactions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Profile\", \"description\": \"This product is high in total fat (33.1g) and saturated fat (12.5g), along with very high sodium (993mg) per serving. These levels are not conducive to a healthy diet and can contribute to cardiovascular risks and inflammation, which may negatively impact hormonal balance.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains several additives including natural/nature identical flavourings, maltodextrin, multiple acidity regulators (330, 296, 334), an anticaking agent (551), and a colorant (160c). While individually many are considered safe, the cumulative effect of consuming a highly processed snack with numerous additives regularly is not ideal for long-term health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Hormonal Impact\", \"description\": \"The high content of saturated fats can contribute to systemic inflammation, potentially exacerbating hormonal imbalances. While sugar content is low, the overall processed nature and high sodium can also subtly impact hormonal regulation and overall well-being. The primary concern, however, remains the gluten content.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"**Strictly AVOID:** Due to the explicit presence of barley, this product is unsafe and must be completely avoided by individuals with gluten sensitivity or celiac disease.\", \"**Seek Certified Gluten-Free Alternatives:** Always look for snack products explicitly labeled and certified as gluten-free to ensure safety and prevent allergic reactions.\", \"**Prioritize Whole, Unprocessed Snacks:** Opt for naturally gluten-free and nutrient-dense options like fresh fruits, vegetables with hummus, nuts, and seeds to support both gluten-free needs and hormonal health.\", \"**Monitor Sodium and Saturated Fat Intake:** Even when choosing gluten-free snacks, be mindful of high sodium and saturated fat levels, as these can contribute to inflammation and impact overall health, including hormonal balance.\"]}', '2026-03-16 06:25:26'),
(2, 1, 'Potato Chips India\'s Masala Magic Flavour', 'Lay\'s', 15, 'HIGH', '1_758fcfce372048569e52943967ed2386.jpg', 'G ingredients photo of\nX\nGrocery: S\nsilkrute.com/grocery/snacks/chips/lays-potato-chips-48-grams-40-grams-8-grams-extra-indias-masala-magic-flavour-crunchy-chips-and-snacks/?srsltid=AfmBOoraM-m519,\nор\nYouTube\nMaps\npullamsettymaanas...\nTotal Sugars\n2.5g\nAdded Sugars\n0.2g\n0%\nTotal Fat\n33.1 g\n10%\nSaturated Fat\n12.5g\n11%\nTrans Fat\n0.1 g\n1%\nSodium\n993 mg\n10%\nApproximate\natoes\nay\'s\nected\nrs and\ntheir\nEaste\nre.\ncom/images/detailed/4192/71p2u3-szxl.jpg\nLay\'s is the Registered Trade Mark of PepsiCo, Inc.\nINGREDIENTS: Potato, Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein,\nRice Bran Oil), \"Seasoning (\"Spices & Condiments,\nlodised Salt, Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical\nFlavouring Substances), Black Salt, Sugar, Tomato\nPowder, Maltodextrin, Acidity Regulators (330, 296, 334),\nAnticaking Agent (551), Colour (160c)).\n\"As flavouring agent. \"Contains Onion and Garlic\nALLERGEN ADVICE: Contains Barley\nPROPRIETARY FOOD - POTATO CHIPS (15.1)\nAs compared to previous Lay\'s India\'s\nMagic Masala packs. Limited period offer,\nvalid in select geographies.\nERING\nWITH\n\'For details on PepsiCo\npartnership with farmers,\nvieit ununu neneicoindia co in\nLay\'s Potato Chips 48 grams (40 grams +8 grams EXTRA) India\'s Masala Magic Flavc\nE', '{\"overall_score\": 15, \"risk_level\": \"HIGH\", \"overview\": \"This product contains barley, which is a direct gluten allergen for you, making it unsuitable for consumption. Beyond the allergen risk, it is a highly processed snack high in saturated fat and sodium, with several artificial and processed ingredients that could negatively impact hormonal balance.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Low\", \"additives_count\": 6, \"allergens_found\": [\"Gluten\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Potato\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural whole food, generally safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Rice Bran Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palmolein is high in saturated fat and processed. High intake of processed oils and saturated fats can contribute to inflammation and may negatively impact hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A broad category, generally safe unless specific allergies are present, which is not the case for this user (beyond gluten).\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The product\'s sodium content (993mg per 48g packet) is very high for a snack. Excessive sodium intake can lead to fluid retention and may indirectly affect overall health and hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical Flavouring Substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"\\\"Nature identical\\\" means synthetic compounds mimicking natural flavors. While generally considered safe by regulators, minimizing processed and artificial additives is often recommended for sensitive individuals and for supporting hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Black Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Adds to the overall sodium content, contributing to the high sodium level of the product.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Although the product lists only 0.2g of added sugars, the presence of \'Sugar\' as an ingredient contributes to overall sugar intake. Excessive sugar can contribute to inflammation and insulin dysregulation, impacting hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tomato Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A dehydrated form of tomato, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Maltodextrin\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"A highly processed carbohydrate with a high glycemic index, which can cause rapid blood sugar spikes. This can be detrimental for insulin sensitivity and overall hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulators (330, 296, 334)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Citric Acid (330), Malic Acid (296), and Tartaric Acid (334) are common and generally safe food acids.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Anticaking Agent (551)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Silicon Dioxide, generally considered safe in the small amounts used in food.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Colour (160c)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Paprika extract, a natural colorant, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Onion and Garlic\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Common food ingredients, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Barley\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"Contains gluten, which is a direct allergen for the user. This makes the product unsuitable for consumption.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Allergen Risk\", \"description\": \"This product carries a high allergen risk due to the explicit presence of \'Barley\' in the ingredient list and allergen advice. Barley contains gluten, which is a known sensitivity for the user, making this product unsafe for consumption.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value & Processing Level\", \"description\": \"This is a highly processed snack food. It is high in total fat (33.1g) and saturated fat (12.5g), contributing to potential cardiovascular concerns if consumed regularly. The sodium content (993mg per 48g packet) is exceptionally high for a single snack serving, representing a significant portion of daily recommended intake. These factors indicate poor nutritional value.\"}, {\"title\": \"Hormonal Impact\", \"description\": \"Beyond the gluten issue, several ingredients could negatively impact hormonal balance. The high saturated fat from palmolein can contribute to inflammation. High sodium intake can affect fluid balance and blood pressure. Maltodextrin, a high-glycemic carbohydrate, can lead to rapid blood sugar spikes, potentially impacting insulin sensitivity and other hormones. Minimizing such processed ingredients is generally beneficial for hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains multiple additives, including \'Nature Identical Flavouring Substances\', several acidity regulators (E330, E296, E334), an anticaking agent (E551), and a color (E160c). While individually deemed safe, a high load of processed additives is generally not recommended for individuals with health conditions or sensitivities.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Absolutely AVOID this product due to the presence of barley, which contains gluten and is a direct allergen for you.\", \"Opt for naturally gluten-free snacks such as fresh fruits, vegetables with hummus, nuts, seeds, or gluten-free crackers.\", \"Prioritize whole, unprocessed foods in your diet to support hormonal health and minimize exposure to additives, excessive sodium, and unhealthy fats.\", \"When choosing packaged snacks, carefully read ingredient labels for hidden gluten sources and a high number of processed ingredients or additives.\", \"Consider making homemade snacks where you have full control over the ingredients to ensure they align with your dietary needs and health goals.\"]}', '2026-03-16 06:31:41'),
(3, 1, 'Potato Chips', 'Lay\'s', 25, 'HIGH', '1_4766aadcd4c448b6877b02a481e54736.jpg', '%RDA Per Serve\nEnergy\nProtein\n538 kcal\n5%\n6.69\nCarbohydrate\n53.99\nTotal Sugars\n2.39\nAdded Sugars\n129\n0%\nTotal Fat\n33.09\n10%\nSaturated Fat\n12.59\n11%\nTrans Fat\n0.19\n1%\nSodium\n555 mg\n6%\nApproximate\n0.41/- PER gl\nLay\'s and Lay\'s Sizzlin\' Hot are Trademarks of PepsiCo, Inc.\nINGREDIENTS: Potato, Edible Vegetable Ol\n(Palmolein, Rice Bran Oil). \"Seasoning (Maltodextrin,\n\"Spices & Condiments, Sugar, lodised Salt, Acidity\nRegulator (330), Dehydrated Vegetable (Beetroot\nPowder), Flavour (Natural Flavouring Substance).\nButter Milk Powder, Anticaking Agent (551), Flavour\nEnhancers (627&631).\n\"As flavouring agent. \"Contains Onion and Garlic\nALLERGEN ADVICE: Contains Milk\nPROPRIETARY FOOD-POTATO CHIPS (15.1)\nWITH\n\"For details on PepsiCo\npartnership with farmers,\nvisit www.pepsicoindia.co.in\nFind us on:\nfacebook.com/laysindia\n83\n12:06\n40) ENG\n16-03-2026', '{\"overall_score\": 25, \"risk_level\": \"HIGH\", \"overview\": \"This product presents a high risk for the user due to the likely presence of gluten from maltodextrin, which directly conflicts with the user\'s gluten allergy. Furthermore, its highly processed nature, high fat content, and added sugars can negatively impact hormonal balance.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"2.3g per serve\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [\"Gluten\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Potato\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural vegetable, generally safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Rice Bran Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are highly processed oils. Palmolein is high in saturated fat, and excessive intake of processed oils can contribute to inflammation, which may negatively impact hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Maltodextrin\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"Maltodextrin is often derived from wheat unless specified otherwise. Without a \'gluten-free\' certification, it poses a direct risk for a user with a gluten allergy. It\'s also a rapidly digested carbohydrate that can spike blood sugar, affecting hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"General term for flavorings, typically safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Added sugar contributes to blood sugar fluctuations and can promote inflammation, potentially affecting hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While essential, the product contains a moderate amount of sodium per serving (555mg), and high intake can contribute to health issues potentially impacting hormonal regulation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulator (330) (Citric Acid)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally recognized as safe (GRAS) and widely used food additive.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Dehydrated Vegetable (Beetroot Powder)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural ingredient, primarily used for color, and generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural Flavouring Substance)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The term \'natural flavouring\' is broad and can encompass various ingredients and processing aids. While generally considered safe, it still represents a processed component.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Butter Milk Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Contains milk, as noted in the allergen advice. However, the user does not have a dairy allergy.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Anticaking Agent (551) (Silicon Dioxide)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered safe in the small amounts used in food products.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour Enhancers (627 & 631) (Disodium Guanylate & Disodium Inosinate)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are processed additives that contribute to the highly processed nature of the food. While generally recognized as safe, individuals with hormonal conditions may benefit from minimizing consumption of such additives.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Onion and Garlic\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavoring ingredients, generally safe.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Allergen Risk (Gluten)\", \"description\": \"The presence of Maltodextrin is a significant concern. Unless explicitly stated as derived from a non-wheat source or certified \'gluten-free,\' it poses a direct and high risk for individuals with a gluten allergy. Consumption could lead to adverse allergic reactions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Profile\", \"description\": \"This product is high in calories (538 kcal), total fat (33g), and carbohydrates (53.9g), with a relatively low protein content (6.6g). It also contains a notable amount of sodium (555mg) and some trans fat (0.1g). This profile makes it a nutritionally poor choice that can contribute to weight gain, inflammation, and blood sugar dysregulation, all of which are detrimental to hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processed Ingredients & Additives\", \"description\": \"The product contains multiple highly processed ingredients, including processed vegetable oils, maltodextrin, natural flavorings, and flavor enhancers (627 & 631). A diet high in ultra-processed foods is associated with poorer health outcomes, including inflammation and metabolic issues, which can negatively impact hormonal balance.\"}, {\"title\": \"Hormonal Impact\", \"description\": \"The combination of high fat (especially saturated and trans fats), added sugars, rapid carbohydrates (maltodextrin), and numerous processed additives can contribute to chronic inflammation, insulin resistance, and blood sugar spikes. These factors are known to disrupt hormonal balance, which is particularly relevant for individuals with hormonal health conditions.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Strictly AVOID this product due to the high risk of gluten exposure from Maltodextrin, which is a direct allergen for your profile.\", \"Prioritize whole, unprocessed foods to support hormonal balance and overall health. Focus on lean proteins, healthy fats, and complex carbohydrates.\", \"Be mindful of processed snacks in general, as their high fat, sugar, and additive content can contribute to inflammation and blood sugar instability.\", \"Always check labels for \'gluten-free\' certification when purchasing packaged foods to ensure safety regarding your allergy.\", \"Consider making your own snacks using fresh ingredients to control sodium, fat, and sugar content, and avoid hidden allergens.\"]}', '2026-03-16 06:36:30'),
(4, 1, 'Smartwater', 'Bisleri', 95, 'LOW', '1_729b7fc426424eda90ef7872e604dc2f.jpg', '10\nTes\n172.31.29.156:5000 ×\nThank you for down! x\nWhatsApp\nX\nMaps\npullamsettymaanas...\nlocalhost/127.0.0.1 ×\nGrocery: Snacks :: C\nX\nG water bttle indgridie X +\nO\nsearch?q=water+bttle+indgridients+&sca_esv=acb1e3fff4658f32&rlz=1C1RLNS_enIN1153IN1153&udm=2&biw=1536&bih=695&sxsrf=ANbL-n6phuSVKhJevjOTXIRmoYDv7z125g%3A177...\nOr\ncalcium\nmagnesium\npookusum\nactrolyte\nectrolytes\nsmartwater\nINGREDIENTS\nVAPOR DISTILLED WATER, CALCIUM\nCHLORIDE AND MAGNESIUM CHLORIDE\nAND POTASSIUM BICARBONATE\n(ELECTROLYTE SOURCES*)\nPACKAGED CHINKING WATER GROMISED\nNENEMENTS TREATED WEILE WASING\nMED BY HISTRY INTERNET WW\nLAZ\nMEL Magazine\nwater bttle indgridients &umgurl=https%3A%2F%2Fmelmagazine.com%2Fwp-content%2Fu\nF2018%2F08%2F1yOVOMMUMNy011 jpeg&reful h\nST\n\"BEST BEFORE SIX MONTHS FROUCUENTORES\nSTORE IN COOL AND DRY PLACE\nKEEP THE CONTAINER WAY FROM CT SUNUGH\nFOR DATE OF MANUFACTURE AND USE BY\nBATCH NO MRP (INCL OF A TAMESE SE\nCONTACT: CUSTOMER CARE EXECUTIVE 800-121-1007 NET\nEMAIL WECARE BISLER.CON\nADDRESS SAME AS MAT RY ADDRESS\n50\nIndiaMART\n40 ENG\nbalded\n1206\n16-01-2026', '{\"overall_score\": 95, \"risk_level\": \"LOW\", \"overview\": \"This product is primarily re-mineralized water, fortified with essential electrolytes. It is an excellent choice for an adult with hormonal conditions and gluten sensitivity, offering hydration and key minerals without any common allergens or problematic additives.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"0g\", \"additives_count\": 0, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Vapor Distilled Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Pure water, essential for hydration, and contains no gluten or known negative impacts on hormonal health. It\'s the primary component of the product.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Calcium Chloride\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A mineral salt providing calcium, which is important for bone health, nerve function, and muscle contraction. It is safe for individuals with gluten sensitivity and generally supports overall physiological functions, including those that influence hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Magnesium Chloride\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A mineral salt providing magnesium, a critical electrolyte involved in over 300 enzymatic reactions in the body, including those related to muscle and nerve function, blood glucose control, and blood pressure regulation. Magnesium is often beneficial for hormonal health. It is safe for gluten-sensitive individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Potassium Bicarbonate\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A mineral salt providing potassium, which is vital for maintaining fluid balance, nerve signals, and muscle contractions. It contributes to overall electrolyte balance, which is supportive of hormonal health. It is safe for gluten-sensitive individuals.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"This product primarily offers hydration and essential electrolytes (calcium, magnesium, potassium). These minerals are vital for various bodily functions and can indirectly support overall health and hormonal balance by preventing dehydration and electrolyte imbalances. It is not a source of calories or macronutrients.\"}, {\"title\": \"Allergen Risk\", \"description\": \"The product poses an extremely low allergen risk. None of the listed ingredients contain gluten, making it perfectly safe for individuals with gluten sensitivity. It is also free from other common allergens.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"This product has no artificial additives, preservatives, colors, or flavors. Calcium chloride, magnesium chloride, and potassium bicarbonate are mineral salts added for their electrolyte properties, not as artificial additives.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The water undergoes vapor distillation for purification, followed by the re-addition of specific mineral salts to replenish electrolytes. This level of processing is minimal and aimed at enhancing its hydration and mineral profile, rather than introducing highly processed components.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Continue to use this product for hydration as it is well-suited for your health profile, providing essential electrolytes without any allergens.\", \"Ensure you maintain a balanced diet rich in whole foods to meet all your nutritional needs, as this water provides only specific minerals.\", \"Stay adequately hydrated throughout the day, as proper fluid and electrolyte balance is crucial for optimal hormonal function.\", \"If you have specific concerns about your hormonal conditions, consult with your healthcare provider or a registered dietitian for personalized dietary and hydration advice.\"]}', '2026-03-16 06:40:16'),
