[\"Gluten\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Potato\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A whole food ingredient, generally well-tolerated and provides some carbohydrates.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Rice Bran Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High in saturated fat (Palmolein) and processed. Excessive intake of unhealthy fats can contribute to inflammation and potentially impact hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered safe. Specific sensitivities are not indicated for generic spices.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The product contains high sodium (993mg per serving), which can contribute to high blood pressure and fluid retention, potentially impacting overall health and indirectly hormonal balance if consumed excessively.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical Flavouring Substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"\\\"Nature identical\\\" flavors are synthetic compounds that mimic natural ones; while often safe, their long-term health effects are less studied than whole foods, and some individuals may react to them.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Black Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Another form of salt, contributing to the overall high sodium content of the product.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While total sugar is low (2.5g), it\'s an added ingredient. Excessive sugar intake, even in small amounts over time, can contribute to blood sugar dysregulation, which impacts hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tomato Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural ingredient generally considered safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Maltodextrin\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"A highly processed carbohydrate with a high glycemic index that can cause rapid spikes in blood sugar, potentially impacting hormonal balance. If derived from barley (given the allergen warning), it would also be a direct gluten source.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulators (330, 296, 334)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are common food acids (Citric Acid, Malic Acid, Tartaric Acid) generally recognized as safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Anticaking Agent (551)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Silicon Dioxide is a commonly used food additive, generally considered safe in the amounts used.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Colour (160c)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Paprika extract is a natural food color derived from paprika, generally considered safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Barley (Allergen)\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"The product explicitly states \'Contains Barley,\' which is a source of gluten and directly triggers your gluten allergy. Consumption must be avoided.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Allergen Risk\", \"description\": \"This product poses a very high allergen risk due to the explicit warning \'Contains Barley.\' Barley contains gluten, which is a direct trigger for your gluten allergy. Ingesting this product could lead to severe allergic reactions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Hormonal Impact\", \"description\": \"Beyond the severe allergen risk, the product contains a significant amount of processed fats (Palmolein) and high sodium. Maltodextrin and added sugars, even in small amounts, can contribute to blood sugar fluctuations, which can negatively impact hormonal balance over time. Regular consumption of such highly processed snacks is not conducive to optimal hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"As a highly processed snack, these chips offer very little nutritional value. They are high in calories, unhealthy fats, and sodium, with minimal beneficial nutrients. They are not recommended as a staple for a healthy diet, especially for individuals with specific health conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains several food additives, including acidity regulators, an anticaking agent, a color, and \'natural and nature identical flavouring substances.\' While individually some may be considered safe, a higher load of such additives is generally found in ultra-processed foods, which are less ideal for overall health and sensitive individuals.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"**Absolutely avoid this product:** Due to the explicit \'Contains Barley\' allergen warning, this product is unsafe for you and must be avoided to prevent an allergic reaction.\", \"Prioritize naturally gluten-free snacks: Opt for snacks explicitly labeled gluten-free, or choose whole foods like fruits, vegetables, nuts, and seeds.\", \"Choose fresh, whole foods for hormonal health: Focus on a diet rich in whole grains (certified gluten-free), lean proteins, healthy fats (avocado, olive oil, nuts), and plenty of fruits and vegetables to support hormonal balance.\", \"Be diligent about reading labels: Always check for allergen warnings and hidden sources of gluten in all packaged foods.\", \"Consider making homemade snacks: This allows you full control over ingredients, ensuring they are gluten-free and tailored to support your hormonal health.\"]}', '2026-03-16 06:40:38'),
(6, 2, 'Vapor Distilled Water with Electrolytes', 'Smartwater', 85, 'LOW', '2_503aed3d4d794b019fde0e562a476e24.jpg', 'GR\ngith x\nMram\nX\nram X\nGit x G wat\n+\n1N4CSCB7_gnyK3vdSfEdMVBw:1773647482013&udm=2&fbs=ADc_l-aNOCWEZBOHjofHoa MMDIK...\nP\nQ\np\nri\nPurified water nutrition facts\nSmart water\nSmartwater\nAquaf\nMEL Magazine\n<\n>\nMADE IN UGO\n30\nURY AND USER\nDEAL TAUST SHE BOU. 1002001539\nCARE EXECUTIVE 1800 121-1007 NET QUANTITY\nBISLER COIN\nMAT BY ADDRESS\n500ml\nMART\nBisleri Water Bottle 5...\nLED WATER, CALCIUM\nOMAGNESIUM CHLORIDE\nM BICARBONATE\nE SOURCES)\nBed Water\nsmartwater\nINGREDIENTS\nVAPOR DISTILLED WATER, CALCIUM\nCHLORIDE AND MAGNESIUM CHLORIDE\nAND POTASSIUM BICARBON TE\n(ELECTROLYTE SOURCES*)\nWhat\'s in This?: Bottled Water\nImages may be subject to copyright Learn more\nShare\nSave\n1,024 × 615\nVisit >\nNutrition Facts\nNutrition Facts\nwith essential\nelectrolytes\nsmartwater antioxidant\n-4) ENG\n13:21\n16-03-2026', '{\"overall_score\": 85, \"risk_level\": \"LOW\", \"overview\": \"This product is primarily vapor-distilled water enhanced with essential electrolytes. For an adult with digestive conditions, it is generally considered safe and can contribute to hydration. While some electrolyte compounds can potentially affect sensitive digestive systems in very high doses, the concentrations in this product are typically low and intended for beneficial replenishment.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"0g\", \"additives_count\": 3, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Vapor Distilled Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Highly purified water, generally safe and beneficial for hydration, especially for individuals with digestive sensitivities as it lacks common impurities that might irritate a sensitive system.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Calcium Chloride\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While generally safe in small amounts as an electrolyte, very high intakes could potentially cause mild digestive discomfort. The amount in electrolyte water is typically low and not expected to cause issues for most.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Magnesium Chloride\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Magnesium salts, in higher concentrations, are known for their laxative effect. While typically present in small, beneficial amounts in electrolyte water, individuals with very sensitive digestive systems should be aware.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Potassium Bicarbonate\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"An essential electrolyte, generally very safe. Bicarbonate can also act as an antacid, potentially offering mild relief for some digestive upset.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Hydration & Electrolyte Balance\", \"description\": \"This product provides vapor-distilled water for hydration and essential electrolytes (calcium, magnesium, potassium). These electrolytes are crucial for bodily functions, including nerve and muscle function, and maintaining fluid balance. For an adult with digestive conditions, proper hydration and electrolyte balance are often beneficial, especially if conditions involve fluid loss.\"}, {\"title\": \"Digestive Impact\", \"description\": \"The primary concern for an adult with digestive issues revolves around the mineral salts (calcium chloride, magnesium chloride). While generally in low, safe concentrations in electrolyte water, magnesium, in particular, can have a laxative effect in higher doses. Individuals with conditions like IBS-D might find excessive consumption problematic, whereas those with constipation might find it mildly beneficial. The highly purified water base is unlikely to cause irritation.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The \'additives\' in this product (calcium chloride, magnesium chloride, potassium bicarbonate) are naturally occurring mineral salts added for their electrolyte properties, not artificial flavors, colors, or preservatives. The additive load is minimal and functional, aiming to enhance the nutritional profile of the water rather than introducing unnecessary synthetic compounds.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"Vapor distillation is a significant purification process, resulting in highly pure water devoid of many minerals and contaminants. Electrolytes are then re-added. This high level of processing for purification can be advantageous for sensitive individuals, as it removes potential irritants found in tap or less-purified bottled waters.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"While generally safe, monitor your body\'s response, especially to the magnesium and calcium content, to ensure it doesn\'t exacerbate any specific digestive sensitivities.\", \"Ensure this water is part of a balanced hydration strategy; occasionally alternating with plain purified water might be beneficial.\", \"If you experience any unusual digestive discomfort after consumption, consider reducing intake or consulting with a healthcare professional or registered dietitian.\", \"Stay consistently hydrated throughout the day, as adequate fluid intake is crucial for healthy digestion.\"]}', '2026-03-16 07:52:56'),
(7, 2, 'Purified Water', 'Member\'s Mark', 67, 'MODERATE', '2_036883f8b3e3497b8bdc3336a1ac5e5c.jpg', 'INGREDIENTS: PURIFIED WATER, CALCIUM\nCHLORIDE, SODIUM BICARBONATE\nDISTRIBUTED BY SAM\'S WEST, INC.\nBENTONVILLE, AR 72716\nPURIFIED BY REVERSE OSMOSIS\nNO BPA ADDED\nWARNING: Cap is a small part and poses a\nCHOKING HAZARD, particularly for children.\nM\nMember\'s ember\'s\nsamsclub.com Mark\nFOR A REPORT\nINFORMATION\nRECYCLABLE\nEMPTY BOTTLE\nPURIFIED AT\nFOR YOUR TRST\nRECYCLE\nFOR THE PLANET', '{\"overall_score\": 67, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product, primarily purified water with added electrolytes (calcium chloride, sodium bicarbonate), is generally safe. However, for individuals with digestive conditions, these mineral salts might cause mild discomfort like bloating or upset stomach if consumed in large quantities.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Low\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Purified Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Essential for hydration and purified by reverse osmosis to remove contaminants, posing no known risks for digestive conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Calcium Chloride\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While generally safe and used as an electrolyte, in some sensitive individuals or in higher amounts, mineral salts like calcium chloride can potentially cause mild digestive upset like stomach irritation or nausea, which could be relevant for someone with pre-existing digestive conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sodium Bicarbonate\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Commonly used as an antacid, but in sensitive individuals or excessive intake, it can lead to side effects such as bloating, gas, or stomach cramps, which could exacerbate pre-existing digestive issues.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Ingredient Purity\", \"description\": \"The primary ingredient is purified water by reverse osmosis, indicating a high standard of purity and removal of contaminants. This is beneficial for general health and unlikely to pose digestive issues.\"}, {\"title\": \"Electrolyte Digestive Impact\", \"description\": \"Calcium chloride and sodium bicarbonate, while functional electrolytes, are mineral salts that could potentially cause mild digestive discomfort (e.g., bloating, gas, upset stomach) in individuals with sensitive digestive systems if consumed in large quantities.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains a minimal number of added ingredients, limited to two functional mineral salts. This represents a low additive load and is generally favorable for digestive health compared to products with numerous synthetic additives.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Begin with small amounts to assess your digestive tolerance to the mineral salts in the product.\", \"Monitor for any signs of digestive discomfort such as bloating, gas, or stomach upset after consumption.\", \"Ensure balanced hydration from various sources, not solely relying on electrolyte-enhanced waters if digestive issues arise.\", \"Consult with a healthcare professional or dietitian if you experience persistent digestive issues or have specific dietary concerns related to your digestive condition.\"]}', '2026-03-16 07:53:12'),
