s lead to constipation or stomach discomfort in sensitive individuals, which is relevant for a user with digestive conditions. The amount in water is usually low, but awareness is advised.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SODIUM BICARBONATE\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Also known as baking soda (E500), this is a mineral salt used as a pH adjuster. In small amounts in water, it can act as an antacid and help balance digestive pH, often beneficial for those with mild indigestion. It is generally considered safe and well-tolerated.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"The product provides hydration along with small amounts of essential electrolytes (calcium and sodium). It is not a significant source of vitamins, macronutrients, or other minerals beyond what is listed, serving primarily as a rehydrating beverage.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The water undergoes significant processing, including reverse osmosis for purification, followed by the reintroduction of specific minerals (calcium chloride, sodium bicarbonate). This makes it a highly processed beverage, albeit one focused on clean hydration.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Profile\", \"description\": \"This product contains two E-numbers (E509 Calcium Chloride and E500 Sodium Bicarbonate). These are mineral salts, not artificial or synthetic compounds, and are generally regarded as safe for consumption. Their inclusion is to provide electrolytes and improve taste.\"}, {\"title\": \"Digestive Impact\", \"description\": \"For individuals with digestive conditions, this water is generally safe and potentially beneficial due to the antacid properties of sodium bicarbonate. However, sensitive individuals should monitor for any constipation or discomfort that could theoretically arise from higher-than-average calcium intake if consumed in very large quantities or combined with other calcium-rich sources.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Monitor your body\'s response, especially if you have sensitive digestive conditions, though side effects from these minerals in water are rare.\", \"Ensure this water contributes to your overall daily hydration needs, as it provides essential electrolytes.\", \"If you experience constipation, consider your total daily calcium intake from all sources (diet, supplements, and beverages).\", \"This product is a suitable choice for general hydration and can be particularly beneficial for replenishing electrolytes after exercise or during illness.\"]}', '2026-03-16 09:19:46');
