(11, 6, 'Purified Water', 'Member\'s Mark', 65, 'MODERATE', '6_c9d395cd0d3e4c47b9bff94b985c46d6.jpg', 'PURI\nFOR\nINGREDIENTS: PURIFIED WATER, CALCIUM\nCHLORIDE, SODIUM BICARBONATE\nDISTRIBUTED BY SAM\'S WEST, INC.\nBENTONVILLE, AR 72716\nPURIFIED BY REVERSE OSMOSIS\nNO BPA ADDED\nWARNING: Cap is a small part and poses a\nCHOKING HAZARD, particularly for children.\nembers\nMember\'s\nsamsclub.Mark\nFOR A REPORT\nINFORMATION\nRE\nFOR T\nRECYCLABLE\nEMPTY BOTT\nOL', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product is primarily purified water with added mineral salts. While generally safe for hydration, the presence of sodium bicarbonate and calcium chloride warrants moderate caution for a senior with cardiovascular conditions due to potential sodium intake and possible interactions with certain medications.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"0g\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Purified Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Essential for hydration and poses no known health concerns for any of the user\'s conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Calcium Chloride\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While calcium is essential, excessive intake or specific forms can interact with certain cardiovascular medications (e.g., calcium channel blockers) or potentially exacerbate some cardiovascular conditions. Seniors, who may be on multiple medications, should consume in moderation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sodium Bicarbonate\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This ingredient contains sodium, which is a significant concern for individuals with cardiovascular conditions, especially those managing hypertension. High sodium intake can contribute to increased blood pressure and fluid retention, which seniors are often advised to limit.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"The product contains no sugar, making it perfectly safe for a user managing blood sugar conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Cardiovascular Impact\", \"description\": \"The presence of sodium bicarbonate contributes sodium, which is a concern for individuals with cardiovascular conditions due to its potential to affect blood pressure. Calcium chloride also introduces minerals that may require consideration for those on specific heart medications.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains two mineral salts (calcium chloride, sodium bicarbonate) which are considered food additives or processing aids. While not artificial in the sense of synthetic colors or flavors, they are added ingredients that contribute to the overall composition.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"This product is essentially water with minimal added minerals, providing hydration but not significant nutritional value beyond that. The added minerals are not in quantities to be considered a primary dietary source.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Monitor your total daily sodium intake from all sources, especially if consuming this product regularly, due to the sodium bicarbonate content.\", \"Consult with your healthcare provider regarding calcium chloride if you are on specific cardiovascular medications (e.g., calcium channel blockers) to understand potential interactions.\", \"Ensure adequate hydration by prioritizing plain, unflavored water without added salts, especially if managing blood pressure.\", \"Always read product labels to understand the full mineral content of bottled waters if you are managing specific health conditions like cardiovascular disease.\"]}', '2026-03-17 06:32:47'),
(14, 6, 'Maggi 2-minute Noodles', 'Maggi', 65, 'MODERATE', '6_3149d3a337ea4f46bf6a22c146d442a6.jpg', 'ents\nINGREDIENTS: WHEAT FLOUR, PALM OIL, SALT,\nAND LESS THAN 2% SUGAR, HYDROLYZED PEANUT\nPROTEIN, ONION POWDER, CORNSTARCH, SPICES,\nWHEAT GLUTEN, POTASSIUM CHLORIDE, CHILI\nPOWDER, TURMERIC, GARLIC POWDER, CITRIC ACID,\nSODIUM TRIPOLYPHOSPHATE, POTASSIUM\nCARBONATE, SODIUM CARBONATE, CARAMEL COLOR,\nDISODIUM GUANYLATE, DISODIUM INOSINATE,\nBAKING SODA UAR GUM, POTASSIUM IODATE\nCONTAINS: WHEAT AND PEANUT.\nMAY CONTAIN MILK AND SOY.\nIndian Market\nMaggi 2-minute Noodles - Indian Market\nJioMart\nINGREDIENTS:\nNoodles: Refined wh\n(508&412 Ac\nMasala Tastemaker\nwheat flour\nIngredients\nHOLDLES', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product, Maggi 2-minute Noodles, is highly processed and contains several ingredients of concern for a senior user with blood sugar and cardiovascular conditions. It is high in refined carbohydrates, saturated fat (palm oil), and likely high in sodium. While suitable for occasional consumption, it is not recommended as a regular part of the diet.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Low (for added sugar)\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [\"Wheat\", \"Peanut\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Refined Wheat Flour\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High glycemic index, can rapidly increase blood sugar levels, problematic for the \'blood_sugar\' condition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Palm Oil\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High in saturated fat, which can negatively impact cardiovascular health by increasing LDL cholesterol, a concern for the \'cardiovascular\' condition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High sodium intake is detrimental to cardiovascular health, especially for seniors, and can worsen the \'cardiovascular\' condition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Simple sugar contributes to blood sugar spikes, directly problematic for the \'blood_sugar\' condition, even if \'less than 2%\'.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Hydrolyzed Peanut Protein\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A protein source. While \'PEANUT\' is a declared allergen, the user has no specified peanut allergy.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Onion Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavoring, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Cornstarch\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Refined carbohydrate, which can impact blood sugar levels, relevant for the \'blood_sugar\' condition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavorings, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Wheat Gluten\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A protein from wheat. While \'WHEAT\' is a declared allergen, the user has no specified wheat allergy.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Potassium Chloride\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Often used as a salt substitute in small amounts or for processing; generally recognized as safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Chili Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavoring, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Turmeric\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural spice, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Garlic Powder\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavoring, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Citric Acid\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Acidity regulator, generally safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sodium Tripolyphosphate\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"A phosphate additive; high intake of phosphates, especially from processed foods, may be linked to cardiovascular concerns and kidney health issues.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Potassium Carbonate\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Acidity regulator, generally safe in food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sodium Carbonate\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Acidity regulator, generally safe in food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caramel Color\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Artificial color; some types may contain 4-MEI, a potential carcinogen in high doses, best to limit artificial colors.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Disodium Guanylate\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Flavor enhancer, contributes to the overall additive load in highly processed foods.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Disodium Inosinate\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Flavor enhancer, similar concerns to Disodium Guanylate, adding to the additive load.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Baking Soda\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Contains sodium, contributing to the overall sodium load, which is a concern for the \'cardiovascular\' condition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Guar Gum\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Thickener, generally recognized as safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Potassium Iodate\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Iodine source, generally safe in food amounts.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar & Carbohydrate Impact\", \"description\": \"The product is primarily composed of refined wheat flour and cornstarch, which are high glycemic index carbohydrates. These can cause rapid spikes in blood sugar, posing a direct risk for the user\'s \'blood_sugar\' condition. While explicit added sugar is \'less than 2%\', the overall carbohydrate load is significant and can negatively affect blood glucose control.\"}, {\"title\": \"Cardiovascular Health Risk\", \"description\": \"With ingredients like palm oil (high in saturated fat) and multiple sodium-containing compounds (salt, baking soda), this product presents a considerable risk for the \'cardiovascular\' condition. High intake of saturated fats can increase LDL cholesterol, and high sodium contributes to elevated blood pressure. Sodium Tripolyphosphate is also a phosphate additive whose high intake has been linked to cardiovascular concerns.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing & Additive Load\", \"description\": \"This is a highly processed food containing several additives. Flavor enhancers (Disodium Guanylate, Disodium Inosinate), artificial color (Caramel Color), and a phosphate additive (Sodium Tripolyphosphate) contribute to a significant additive load. While individual additives might be safe in small amounts, their cumulative effect in a highly processed diet, especially for seniors, is a concern.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"The product offers limited nutritional value. It is low in essential fiber, vitamins, and minerals, primarily providing refined carbohydrates and fats. For seniors, prioritizing nutrient-dense foods is crucial for overall health and managing existing conditions. This product is largely composed of \'empty calories\' that do not support optimal health.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consume this product very infrequently and in small portions due to its high content of refined carbohydrates, saturated fat, and sodium, which are detrimental to your \'blood_sugar\' and \'cardiovascular\' conditions.\", \"Always pair instant noodles with significant additions of fresh or frozen non-starchy vegetables and a lean protein source (e.g., boiled egg, chicken breast, tofu) to improve nutritional balance and slow down blood sugar absorption.\", \"Be diligent in checking the nutrition facts label for sodium content when consuming similar products, aiming for low-sodium options to protect your cardiovascular health.\", \"Consider healthier alternatives such as whole-wheat pasta with homemade sauce, brown rice noodles, or broth-based soups with plenty of vegetables and protein to minimize processing and maximize nutritional value.\", \"Consult with a healthcare professional or registered dietitian for personalized dietary advice tailored to your specific \'blood_sugar\' and \'cardiovascular\' conditions.\"]}', '2026-03-17 08:27:38'),
(15, 8, 'Multigrain Instant Noodles', '', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_2e0ed5a86cbb44ee8ecf7232859925e4.jpg', 'THE NOODLES CONTAIN 40% MILLETS\nIngredients: Noodles (83%)\nMultigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\n(78.5%), Thickener (Guar gum), lodised Salt, Antioxidant\n(Natural Rosemary).\nSeasoning (17%)\nNatural Flavoring Substances, Mixed Spices (Onion,\nCoriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed,\nFenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom,\nNutmeg), Tapioca Starch, Desi Khand, lodized Salt, Edible\nVegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil), Acidity Regulator (Citric\nacid), Raising Agent (Baking soda), Thickener (Guar\ngum), Natural Color (Paprika extract).\nAllergen Note\nContains wheat.', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product presents a mixed profile for an adult with hormonal conditions. While it incorporates beneficial whole grains like jowar and a rich blend of anti-inflammatory spices, the presence of added sugar (Desi Khand) and a high omega-6 oil (Sunflower Oil) are key areas of concern. These ingredients could potentially impact blood sugar regulation and inflammation, which are important factors in hormonal balance.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Contains added sugar (Desi Khand), suggesting moderate sugar content.\", \"additives_count\": 5, \"allergens_found\": [\"Wheat\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Multigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Whole wheat is a whole grain, generally beneficial. However, for some with hormonal imbalances, gluten-containing grains can sometimes exacerbate inflammation, though \'whole wheat\' is better than refined. Jowar is a good, gluten-free addition.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Thickener (Guar gum)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally safe and acts as a fiber and thickener. No known adverse effects for hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Essential mineral for thyroid function, which is critical for hormonal health. Generally safe in moderation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Antioxidant (Natural Rosemary)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural extract with antioxidant benefits, generally considered safe and potentially beneficial for reducing oxidative stress.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavoring Substances\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While \'natural,\' the specific compounds are not disclosed. Some natural flavors can still be processed or contain hidden ingredients that might impact sensitive individuals or those with hormonal imbalances.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Mixed Spices (Onion, Coriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed, Fenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom, Nutmeg)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A rich blend of spices, many known for anti-inflammatory properties and potential benefits for hormonal balance (e.g., turmeric, fenugreek, ginger).\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tapioca Starch\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common, gluten-free thickener and binding agent. Generally well-tolerated.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Desi Khand\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"An unrefined form of sugar, but still an added sugar. High sugar intake can negatively impact insulin sensitivity and exacerbate hormonal imbalances, so moderation is key for hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Sunflower oil is high in omega-6 fatty acids. An imbalanced omega-6 to omega-3 ratio can be pro-inflammatory, which may be a consideration for managing hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulator (Citric acid)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Naturally occurring acid, commonly used as a food additive and generally recognized as safe. No known negative impact on hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Raising Agent (Baking soda)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Common leavening agent, generally safe and not associated with hormonal issues.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Color (Paprika extract)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural coloring derived from paprika, generally safe and offers some antioxidant properties.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"The product contains \'Desi Khand,\' an added sugar. While it\'s an unrefined form, any added sugar can significantly impact blood glucose levels and insulin sensitivity. For individuals managing hormonal health, stable blood sugar is crucial, as fluctuations can exacerbate conditions like PCOS or contribute to general hormonal imbalances.\"}, {\"title\": \"Fat Profile & Inflammation\", \"description\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil) is primarily composed of omega-6 fatty acids. While essential, a high dietary intake of omega-6s relative to omega-3s can promote systemic inflammation. Chronic inflammation is a known factor that can negatively influence hormonal balance, making this an area of caution for someone with hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load & Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The product includes several thickeners (Guar gum), an antioxidant (Natural Rosemary), acidity regulators (Citric acid), and natural flavorings. While most of these are naturally derived and generally safe, the presence of multiple additives and \'Natural Flavoring Substances\' suggests a moderate level of processing and introduces some unknowns about their full impact on sensitive individuals.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional & Hormonal Impact\", \"description\": \"On the positive side, the inclusion of whole wheat and jowar (millet) provides valuable fiber and complex carbohydrates, which support gut health and steady energy. The diverse spice blend is rich in compounds with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, some (like fenugreek and turmeric) having specific Traditional/Ayurvedic uses for hormonal support. These positives are somewhat offset by the added sugar and potentially inflammatory oil.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consume this product in moderation, mindful of its contribution to your daily added sugar and omega-6 intake, especially if you are actively managing hormonal imbalances.\", \"To balance the meal, pair these noodles with lean protein and plenty of non-starchy vegetables to increase fiber and nutrient density, and to help mitigate blood sugar spikes.\", \"Consider incorporating sources of omega-3 fatty acids (e.g., flaxseeds, chia seeds, fatty fish) into your overall diet to help balance the omega-6 from sunflower oil and reduce potential inflammatory impact.\", \"Monitor your body\'s response, especially concerning energy levels, blood sugar fluctuations, or any inflammatory symptoms, as individual sensitivities can vary.\", \"If you regularly consume similar convenience foods, look for options with lower added sugar content and alternative oils with a better omega-3 to omega-6 ratio (e.g., olive oil or avocado oil).\"]}', '2026-03-17 10:28:25'),
(17, 8, 'Instant Noodles', 'Slurrp Farm', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_17a0faa70a6046b6bec557b1d4707e42.jpg', 'SS\nslurrp\na\nTools\n4\nSlurrp Farm\nO\nA\nP\nSaves\n> X\nTHE NOODLES CONTAIN 40% MILLETS\nIngredients: Noodles (83%)\nMultigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\n(78.5%), Thickener (Guar gum), lodised Salt, Antioxidant\n(Natural Rosemary).\nSeasoning (17%)\nNatural Flavoring Substances, Mixed Spices (Onion,\nCoriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed,\nFenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom,\nNutmeg), Tapioca Starch, Desi Khand, lodized Salt, Edible\nVegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil), Acidity Regulator (Citric\nacid), Raising Agent (Baking soda), Thickener (Guar\ngum), Natural Color (Paprika extract).\nAllergen Note\nContains wheat.\nInstant Noodles - Serves 2 (Pack of 1)\nImages may be subject to copyright. Learn more\nㄖ0\nShare\nSave\n1,500 - 1.500\nVisit >\n16:00\n40) ENG\n17-03-2026', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This instant noodle product offers a healthier base due to its multigrain content (millets and whole wheat). However, the inclusion of added sugar (Desi Khand) and high omega-6 sunflower oil warrants caution, especially for individuals managing hormonal conditions.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Moderate\", \"additives_count\": 6, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Multigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Whole grains and millets provide fiber and nutrients, supporting stable blood sugar and overall health, which is beneficial for hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Thickener (Guar gum)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A commonly used fiber-based thickener, generally recognized as safe and unlikely to impact hormonal conditions in typical food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Iodine is essential for healthy thyroid function, a key aspect of hormonal health. Consume in moderation due to sodium content.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Antioxidant (Natural Rosemary)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural antioxidant with potential health benefits; poses no known risk to hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavoring Substances\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The exact components are unspecified. While generally safe, some individuals with health conditions prefer to avoid vague ingredients where precise effects are unknown.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Mixed Spices (Onion, Coriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed, Fenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom, Nutmeg)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural spices offer various potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory properties, and are generally beneficial or neutral for hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tapioca Starch\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common starch used as a thickener; generally safe but contributes to the overall carbohydrate load.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Desi Khand\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is an added sugar. High intake of added sugars can negatively impact insulin sensitivity and disrupt hormonal balance, particularly relevant for individuals managing hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High in omega-6 fatty acids. An excessive intake relative to omega-3s may promote inflammation, which can adversely affect hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulator (Citric acid)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common and generally safe food additive, naturally found in citrus fruits.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Raising Agent (Baking soda)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common and generally safe leavening agent.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Color (Paprika extract)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural food coloring, generally safe.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar and Hormonal Balance\", \"description\": \"The presence of Desi Khand (unrefined cane sugar) as an added sweetener is a concern. High sugar intake can lead to insulin resistance and inflammation, which directly impact hormonal regulation. For someone with hormonal conditions, minimizing added sugars is generally recommended.\"}, {\"title\": \"Fat Profile and Inflammation\", \"description\": \"The use of Sunflower Oil, which is rich in omega-6 fatty acids, should be considered. While essential, an imbalance with omega-3 fatty acids can promote systemic inflammation. Chronic inflammation can negatively affect hormonal pathways and overall health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level and Additive Load\", \"description\": \"As an instant noodle product, it is inherently processed. It contains several functional additives like thickeners (Guar gum), an antioxidant (Natural Rosemary), natural flavoring substances, an acidity regulator (Citric acid), a raising agent (Baking soda), and a natural color (Paprika extract). While most are considered safe, a diet rich in minimally processed foods is typically advised for hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Quality (Relative)\", \"description\": \"Compared to traditional refined flour instant noodles, the inclusion of whole wheat and jowar (millets) significantly boosts the fiber and nutrient content, making it a relatively healthier option within its product category. However, it remains a discretionary food item rather than a whole food.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consume this product in moderation, rather than as a daily staple, to help manage overall sugar and omega-6 intake.\", \"Enhance the meal by adding fresh vegetables and a lean protein source (e.g., boiled egg, tofu) to increase nutrient density and fiber, which helps balance blood sugar response.\", \"Be vigilant about your total daily sugar consumption from all food sources, as accumulated intake can significantly impact hormonal health.\", \"If frequently consuming processed foods, consider opting for cooking oils lower in omega-6 and higher in omega-3 (like olive oil or flaxseed oil) in other homemade meals to help balance your fat intake.\", \"For precise nutritional information relevant to your conditions, refer to the full nutritional label when available and consult with a healthcare professional or dietitian.\"]}', '2026-03-17 10:34:04'),
(18, 8, 'Masala Magic Naggii', 'Maggi', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_4a5a875de5d6459b90679f9ba3ff8caf.jpg', 'maggi ingredients - Google Se X\neMaggi Masala-ae-Magic Review X\n+\n18/07/maggi-masala-ae-magic-review.html\namsettymaanas...\nand most of our cooking involves adding a range of spice powders, I was wondering why there is a need to add a\nsachet of Maggi masala.\nINGREDIENTS: Mixed spices ((38.7%) (Red chilli powder (7%), Onion powder\nCumin powder (5.2%), Garlic powder, Coriander powder, Capsicum extract\nTurmeric powder (3.5%), Aniseed (1.4%), Black pepper powder (0.9%),\nFenugreek powder (0.7%), Ginger powder, Clove powder (0.3%), Green\ncardamom powder (0.3%), Nutmeg powder (0.3%), Coriander extract &\nCumin extract)), Salt, Sugar, Flavour enhancer (635), Palm oil, Edible starch\nAcidity regulator (330), Minerals, Caramel salt mix (Salt, Colour (150) &\nPalm oil) and Vitamin A.\nCONTAINS PERMITTED NATURAL COLOUR AND ADDED FLAVOUR\nNATURAL FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\nMAY CONTAIN GLUTEN, MILK, MUSTARD AND SOYA.\nScreenshot taken from Amazon on 6th Jul 2018\nAs always, I turned to the ingredients list:\nGarlic powder, Coriander', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This spice mix contains a variety of natural spices which are generally beneficial. However, it also includes added sugar, salt, palm oil (a source of saturated fat), and several food additives. While none of the ingredients are explicitly harmful for an adult with hormonal conditions, its processed nature and additive load suggest moderation.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Low to Moderate per serving\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [\"Gluten\", \"Milk\", \"Mustard\", \"Soya\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Mixed spices (Red chilli powder, Onion powder, Cumin powder, Garlic powder, Coriander powder, Capsicum extract, Turmeric powder, Aniseed, Black pepper powder, Fenugreek powder, Ginger powder, Clove powder, Green cardamom powder, Nutmeg powder, Coriander extract & Cumin extract)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are natural spices, many of which are known for their anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, potentially beneficial for overall health and supporting hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High sodium intake can contribute to fluid retention and elevated blood pressure, which is generally not ideal for overall health, including hormonal well-being.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Excessive sugar consumption can lead to insulin resistance, inflammation, and energy crashes, all of which can negatively impact hormonal balance over time.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour enhancer (635)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is an artificial additive (Disodium 5\'-ribonucleotides). While generally recognized as safe, minimizing intake of processed additives is often recommended for those focusing on hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Palm oil\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palm oil is high in saturated fat. While necessary in moderation, excessive intake of saturated fats can contribute to inflammation and cardiovascular concerns, indirectly impacting overall health and hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible starch\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common thickening agent, generally safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity regulator (330)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Citric acid is a common and generally safe food additive, often naturally occurring.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Minerals\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A broad term, but generally refers to added micronutrients, which are usually beneficial or neutral.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caramel salt mix (Salt, Colour (150) & Palm oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Includes additional salt and palm oil (already noted) and Colour (150), which is caramel colour. While generally safe, it\'s an unnecessary additive, and some forms may contain trace compounds that some prefer to avoid.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Vitamin A\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"An essential nutrient vital for various bodily functions, generally beneficial.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Added flavour (Natural flavouring substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While described as \'natural,\' the specific components are not disclosed. It\'s a processed ingredient, and minimizing such ingredients is prudent for those managing hormonal conditions.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains several additives, including a flavor enhancer (635), caramel color (150), and unspecified \'added flavour.\' While these are permitted, a higher intake of processed foods with numerous additives is generally discouraged for optimal health, particularly when managing hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Sugar and Sodium Content\", \"description\": \"Both sugar and salt are listed among the top ingredients. While quantities per serving in a spice mix might be low, regular consumption of products high in added sugar and sodium can negatively impact insulin sensitivity, inflammation, blood pressure, and fluid balance, all of which can influence hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processed Fat Content\", \"description\": \"Palm oil is present as a source of fat. It is high in saturated fat. While not inherently bad in small amounts, an overall diet high in saturated and processed fats can contribute to systemic inflammation and may not be ideal for supporting healthy hormonal function.\"}, {\"title\": \"Potential Allergens (Cross-Contamination)\", \"description\": \"The label explicitly states \'MAY CONTAIN GLUTEN, MILK, MUSTARD AND SOYA.\' While the user has no specified allergies, this is an important consideration for general awareness and for individuals who may develop sensitivities or have undiagnosed intolerances.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Use this spice mix in moderation as part of a balanced diet that prioritizes whole, unprocessed foods.\", \"Be mindful of overall sugar and sodium intake from all food sources, as this mix contributes to both.\", \"Consider making homemade spice blends where possible to reduce exposure to additives and control ingredient quality.\", \"Pay attention to how your body responds; if any specific ingredients seem to exacerbate hormonal symptoms, consider reducing or eliminating them.\"]}', '2026-03-18 04:31:56'),
(20, 8, 'Millets Noodles', '', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_eb213e4885744ece986765483f3631dc.jpg', 'THE NOODLES CONTAIN 40% MILLETS\nIngredients: Noodles (83%)\nMultigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\n(78.5%), Thickener (Guar gum), lodised Salt, Antioxidant\n(Natural Rosemary).\nSeasoning (17%)\nNatural Flavoring Substances, Mixed Spices (Onion,\nCoriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed,\nFenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom,\nNutmeg), Tapioca Starch, Desi Khand, lodized Salt, Edible\nVegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil), Acidity Regulator (Citric\nacid), Raising Agent (Baking soda), Thickener (Guar\ngum), Natural Color (Paprika extract).\nAllergen Note\nContains wheat.', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product offers some nutritional benefits through millets and whole grains, providing fiber and beneficial spices. However, it contains added sugar (Desi Khand), refined starch (tapioca), and sunflower oil high in omega-6, which warrant caution for individuals with hormonal conditions due to potential impacts on blood sugar and inflammation.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Moderate\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [\"Wheat\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Multigrain Flour blend (Whole Wheat Flour, Jowar flour)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Provides dietary fiber and complex carbohydrates beneficial for sustained energy and gut health, which indirectly supports hormonal balance. Millets (jowar) are also good for blood sugar regulation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Guar gum\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural thickener that acts as a soluble fiber, potentially aiding digestion and promoting satiety without negative effects on hormonal health in typical food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Excessive sodium intake can contribute to fluid retention and may impact blood pressure. While iodine is essential, high salt intake should be moderated to support overall health and prevent indirect hormonal disruptions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Antioxidant (Natural Rosemary)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural antioxidant that can offer anti-inflammatory benefits, which is generally supportive of overall health and may indirectly benefit hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavoring Substances\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The exact composition is often proprietary. While \'natural,\' some substances can be highly processed or derived from questionable sources, and for hormonal health, it\'s generally best to favor whole, unprocessed foods.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Mixed Spices (Onion, Coriander, Chilli, Turmeric, Garlic, Cumin, Aniseed, Fenugreek, Black Pepper, Ginger, Clove, Cardamom, Nutmeg)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These spices are rich in antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds, many of which can positively influence metabolic health and indirectly support hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Tapioca Starch\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"A refined carbohydrate that can cause rapid blood sugar spikes. For individuals with hormonal conditions, maintaining stable blood sugar is crucial to prevent insulin resistance and hormonal dysregulation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Desi Khand\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is a form of added sugar. High intake of added sugars can lead to insulin resistance, inflammation, and disrupt hormonal balance, particularly relevant for conditions like PCOS or metabolic syndrome.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Sunflower Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Sunflower oil is high in omega-6 fatty acids. While essential, an imbalance with omega-3s can promote inflammation, which is detrimental to overall health and can exacerbate hormonal issues.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulator (Citric acid)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common and generally safe food additive, naturally found in citrus fruits, with no known adverse effects on hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Raising Agent (Baking soda)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Sodium bicarbonate is a common and generally safe leavening agent with no known negative impact on hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Color (Paprika extract)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A natural food coloring derived from paprika, generally considered safe and without adverse effects on hormonal health.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar and Carbohydrate Impact\", \"description\": \"The product contains Desi Khand (added sugar) and Tapioca Starch (refined carbohydrate). For individuals with hormonal conditions, managing blood sugar levels is paramount. Frequent consumption of added sugars and refined starches can lead to insulin spikes, potentially worsening insulin resistance and disrupting delicate hormonal balances. While millets and whole wheat provide beneficial complex carbs, the added simple sugars and starches are a point of concern.\"}, {\"title\": \"Fat Profile and Inflammation\", \"description\": \"The inclusion of Sunflower Oil, which is high in omega-6 fatty acids, raises a moderate concern. An excessive intake of omega-6s relative to omega-3s can promote systemic inflammation. Chronic inflammation is known to negatively impact various aspects of health, including hormonal regulation and endocrine function, making dietary fat balance important for hormonal health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive and Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The product includes several additives like guar gum (E412), citric acid (E330), baking soda (E500), and paprika extract (E160c), which are generally considered safe. However, the presence of \'Natural Flavoring Substances\' represents a less transparent ingredient. While the product utilizes whole grains, the overall processing level is moderate due to the inclusion of starches, oils, and various additives, suggesting it\'s not a whole-food dominant option.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value and Fiber Content\", \"description\": \"The noodles feature a significant portion of millets and whole wheat, offering valuable dietary fiber and a broader nutrient profile compared to refined wheat products. This fiber content is beneficial for gut health, satiety, and blood sugar management, all of which indirectly support hormonal health. The inclusion of a wide array of spices also adds beneficial micronutrients and antioxidants.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Monitor portion sizes to control intake of added sugars and refined carbohydrates, crucial for maintaining stable blood sugar levels and supporting hormonal balance.\", \"Pair this product with lean protein and plenty of non-starchy vegetables to further mitigate blood sugar spikes and enhance nutrient intake.\", \"Be mindful of your overall dietary fat balance, aiming to reduce other sources of high omega-6 oils and increasing omega-3 rich foods (e.g., fatty fish, flaxseeds) to combat potential inflammation.\", \"Consider this an occasional food rather than a daily staple, prioritizing whole, unprocessed foods for the majority of your meals to optimize hormonal health.\", \"Stay hydrated and ensure adequate intake of micronutrients to support overall metabolic and endocrine function.\"]}', '2026-03-18 05:52:47'),
(23, 6, 'PEPSI-COLA', 'PEPSI', 25, 'HIGH', '6_50c7b64821044ef887524917cb0f9341.jpg', 'COLA FLAVOURED SOFT DRINK\nIngredients: Carbonated Water, Sugar,\nCaramel Colour (E150d), Phosphoric Acid,\nCaffeine, Natural Flavourings. Bottled by\nSimonds Farsons Cisk Plc, The Brewery,\nMdina road, Mriehel, Malta, BKR3000,\nunder authority of PepsiCo, Inc., N.Y., USA.\nMalta freephone 8007 4403. For best before\ndate-see neck of bottle. PEPSI, PEPSI-COLA\nand the Pepsi Globe are registered trademarks\nof PepsiCo, Inc. Store in a cool, dry place\nand protect from heat and sunlight\nPEPSI-CLA\nwww.p', '{\"overall_score\": 25, \"risk_level\": \"HIGH\", \"overview\": \"This cola-flavored soft drink is highly problematic for a senior individual with existing blood sugar and cardiovascular conditions. Its primary risks stem from the very high sugar content, which directly exacerbates both conditions, alongside other concerning additives like caffeine and phosphoric acid.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High (approx. 35g per 330ml serving)\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Carbonated Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"No known adverse health effects for this user\'s profile.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"Extremely high sugar content directly contributes to elevated blood sugar levels, worsening diabetes management. It also negatively impacts cardiovascular health by increasing risk factors like obesity, high triglycerides, and inflammation. This is highly detrimental for an individual with blood sugar and cardiovascular conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caramel Colour (E150d)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This specific caramel coloring (sulfite ammonia caramel) can contain 4-methylimidazole (4-MEI), a potential carcinogen. While consumption levels are key, it is an unnecessary additive and generally advisable to limit exposure, especially for seniors with existing health concerns.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Phosphoric Acid\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High intake of phosphoric acid can negatively impact bone density, which is a significant concern for seniors prone to osteoporosis. It has also been linked to kidney stones and potential cardiovascular issues with excessive consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caffeine\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"As a stimulant, caffeine can increase heart rate and blood pressure, which poses a risk for individuals with cardiovascular conditions. Moderation or avoidance is recommended.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavourings\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally recognized as safe and do not pose specific risks for this user\'s profile.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"This product is extremely high in sugar, listed as the second ingredient. For an individual with blood sugar issues, this will cause rapid spikes in blood glucose, making it highly unsuitable. For cardiovascular health, high sugar intake is strongly linked to increased risk of heart disease, obesity, and type 2 diabetes.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product contains Caramel Colour (E150d) and Phosphoric Acid. E150d, while approved, is a chemical additive with some controversy regarding 4-MEI. Phosphoric acid can affect bone health and has been linked to kidney and cardiovascular concerns with high intake. These additives contribute to the product\'s overall low nutritional quality and potential risks.\"}, {\"title\": \"Cardiovascular and Blood Sugar Impact\", \"description\": \"Beyond sugar, caffeine can elevate heart rate and blood pressure, directly impacting cardiovascular health. The combination of high sugar, caffeine, and phosphoric acid makes this product particularly detrimental for someone managing both blood sugar and cardiovascular conditions. It offers no nutritional benefits and significant health risks.\"}, {\"title\": \"Overall Processing Level\", \"description\": \"This is a highly processed beverage, offering \'empty calories\' with no significant nutritional value (vitamins, minerals, fiber). Processed drinks like this contribute to a less healthy diet and can displace more nutritious food and drink choices crucial for managing chronic conditions in seniors.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Strongly advise against consuming this product due to its very high sugar content and other concerning ingredients.\", \"Opt for plain water, unsweetened tea, or naturally flavored water as healthier hydration alternatives.\", \"Consult with a healthcare provider or registered dietitian for personalized dietary advice to manage blood sugar and cardiovascular health.\", \"Prioritize whole, unprocessed foods and beverages that support stable blood sugar and heart health.\", \"Be diligent in checking ingredient labels for added sugars (under various names), caffeine, and artificial additives in all food and drink products.\"]}', '2026-03-18 06:43:05'),
(24, 8, 'PEPSI-COLA', 'PEPSI', 55, 'MODERATE', '8_87be87ab90c445248575b72378a0344c.jpg', 'COLA FLAVOURED SOFT DRINK\nIngredients: Carbonated Water, Sugar,\nCaramel Colour (E150d), Phosphoric Acid,\nCaffeine, Natural Flavourings. Bottled by\nSimonds Farsons Cisk Plc, The Brewery,\nMdina road, Mriehel, Malta, BKR3000,\nunder authority of PepsiCo, Inc., N.Y., USA.\nMalta freephone 8007 4403. For best before\ndate-see neck of bottle. PEPSI, PEPSI-COLA\nand the Pepsi Globe are registered trademarks\nof PepsiCo, Inc. Store in a cool, dry place\nand protect from heat and sunlight\nPEPSI-CLA\nwww.p', '{\"overall_score\": 55, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This cola-flavoured soft drink contains several ingredients that could potentially be of concern for an adult, particularly someone managing hormonal conditions. Its high sugar content and the presence of caffeine and certain additives may warrant mindful consumption. While occasional intake might not be an issue for some, regular consumption could potentially contribute to various health considerations.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Carbonated Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Carbonated water is generally considered safe for consumption and is the primary base for this beverage.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High sugar intake may influence blood sugar levels and energy fluctuations, which could potentially have an indirect impact on hormonal balance and overall well-being for an adult with hormonal conditions. Excessive consumption is often linked to various health concerns.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caramel Colour (E150d)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caramel Colour E150d is an artificial food colouring. While generally recognized as safe, some studies have explored its potential health implications. For individuals aiming to minimize artificial additives, it could be a component to be mindful of.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Phosphoric Acid\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Phosphoric acid is used as a flavouring and preservative. High consumption over time might potentially affect mineral balance, particularly calcium absorption, which could be a concern for some individuals. However, the amounts in soft drinks are generally considered safe for most.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caffeine\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caffeine is a stimulant that can potentially impact sleep patterns, anxiety levels, and stress responses in some individuals. These effects could indirectly influence hormonal balance for an adult with hormonal conditions, suggesting moderation may be beneficial.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavourings\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Natural flavourings are generally considered safe. Their specific composition is not detailed, but they are typically derived from natural sources to enhance taste.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"This product contains a high amount of sugar, which could lead to rapid increases in blood glucose. For an adult with hormonal conditions, maintaining stable blood sugar levels may be supportive of hormonal balance, and high sugar intake could potentially contribute to energy crashes or metabolic considerations over time.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The soft drink contains Caramel Colour (E150d) and Phosphoric Acid. While these additives are approved for use, some individuals may prefer to limit their intake of artificial colours and acids. The long-term effects of consuming multiple additives regularly are an area that some health-conscious individuals might consider.\"}, {\"title\": \"Stimulant Content\", \"description\": \"The presence of caffeine means this beverage could have stimulant effects. For an adult with hormonal conditions, particularly if sensitive to caffeine, this might potentially affect sleep quality, increase feelings of anxiety, or influence stress responses, all of which could indirectly impact hormonal regulation.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"This product primarily offers sugar and water, with minimal to no essential nutrients, vitamins, or minerals. From a nutritional perspective, it is largely considered a source of \'empty calories\' and may not contribute significantly to overall dietary health or satiety.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"You may want to consider limiting your consumption of this product due to its high sugar content, which could potentially impact blood sugar stability and energy levels.\", \"It might be helpful to monitor your intake of caffeine, especially if you are sensitive to its effects or notice any impact on your sleep quality or stress levels, as these factors could influence hormonal balance.\", \"Opting for water, herbal teas, or unsweetened beverages could potentially be a more hydrating and supportive choice for your overall well-being and hormonal health.\", \"If you are aiming to minimize artificial ingredients, you may want to be mindful of the caramel colour and phosphoric acid present in this drink.\"]}', '2026-03-18 08:21:14');
INSERT INTO `scans` (`id`, `user_id`, `product_name`, `brand_name`, `score`, `risk_level`, `image_path`, `raw_ocr_text`, `ai_analysis`, `scanned_at`) VALUES
(26, 8, 'Cola Drink', 'CHINDUSTAN COOL', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_b054adea4c8d484db3471ffd40805745.jpg', 'INGREDIENTS: CARBONATED WATER, SUGAR, ACIDITY\nREGULATOR (338), CAFFEINE (8.1mg/100g), SWEETENE\nCOLOUR (150d), FLAVOURS (NATURAL, NATURE-IDENTI\nARTIFICIAL (COLA) FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)..\nNUTRITION INFORMATION (APPROXIMATE VALUES)\nSERVING-200 ml: 1.5 SERVINGS IN THIS PACK\nPER 100ml\n%RDA*\nPER SERVE\n39 kcal\n3.9%\nENERGY\nCARBOHYDRATE\n9.7 g\nTOTAL SUGARS\n9.5g\nB\n-ADDED SUGARS\n9.5 g\n38%\nTOTAL FAT\n09\n0%\n4\nPROTEIN\nOg\nSODIUM\n22 mg\n2.2%\nMANUFACTURED BY\nCHINDUSTAN COOL', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This beverage contains notable amounts of added sugars, caffeine, and several artificial additives, which could potentially be a consideration for individuals with hormonal conditions. While generally safe for occasional consumption, regular intake might not be ideal.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"19g\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"CARBONATED WATER\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered safe for consumption by most adults and is not typically associated with hormonal concerns.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SUGAR\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The product contains 19g of added sugars per 200ml serving. High intake of added sugars may potentially contribute to blood sugar fluctuations, which could indirectly influence hormonal balance in some individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"ACIDITY REGULATOR (338) (Phosphoric Acid)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While often recognized as safe in moderation, frequent consumption of phosphoric acid might be a concern for some individuals, and it is an artificial additive.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"CAFFEINE\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caffeine intake, even in moderate amounts (16.2mg per 200ml serving), could potentially influence hormonal balance and sleep patterns in some sensitive individuals, which might be a consideration for those with existing hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SWEETENER\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The specific type of artificial sweetener is unspecified. Some artificial sweeteners have been associated with potential changes in gut microbiota and metabolic responses in certain individuals, which might indirectly relate to hormonal regulation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"COLOUR (150d) (Sulphite Ammonia Caramel)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Artificial colors, such as Sulphite Ammonia Caramel, are additives that some individuals might prefer to limit, although a direct impact on hormonal conditions is not typically suggested.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FLAVOURS (NATURAL, NATURE-IDENTICAL, ARTIFICIAL (COLA) FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This ingredient includes artificial flavoring substances, which are additives. Some individuals with hormonal sensitivities might prefer to reduce their intake of artificial ingredients.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"This product contains 19 grams of added sugars per 200ml serving, which could potentially contribute significantly to daily sugar intake. High sugar consumption is often linked to blood sugar spikes, which might have implications for hormonal regulation in some individuals.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The beverage includes several additives such as Acidity Regulator (338), an unspecified Sweetener, Colour (150d), and Artificial Flavouring Substances. While generally approved for consumption, some individuals, especially those with hormonal sensitivities, may prefer to limit their intake of such processed ingredients.\"}, {\"title\": \"Caffeine Content\", \"description\": \"With 16.2 mg of caffeine per 200ml serving, this product contains a relatively low amount compared to some other caffeinated beverages. However, caffeine intake could potentially influence sleep quality and hormonal balance in sensitive individuals, which might be a consideration for those managing hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"As a carbonated soft drink with added sugars, artificial sweeteners, colors, and flavors, this product could be considered highly processed. A diet rich in highly processed foods may not be ideal for optimal health and might indirectly affect overall well-being, including hormonal aspects.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consider consuming this product in moderation, particularly due to its added sugar and additive content, which may not be ideal for frequent intake.\", \"You may want to explore beverages with lower or no added sugars and fewer artificial ingredients as alternatives, especially if managing hormonal conditions.\", \"Be mindful of your total daily caffeine intake from all sources, as caffeine could potentially influence hormonal balance in some individuals.\", \"Prioritize water and herbal teas as primary hydration sources, which are generally considered more beneficial for overall health and hormonal well-being.\"]}', '2026-03-18 08:25:24'),
(27, 8, 'Cola Soft Drink', 'CHINDUSTAN COOL', 58, 'MODERATE', '8_68ac2d412bb5420bb7f72a18ff134907.jpg', 'INGREDIENTS: CARBONATED WATER, SUGAR, ACIDITY\nREGULATOR (338), CAFFEINE (8.1mg/100g), SWEETENE\nCOLOUR (150d), FLAVOURS (NATURAL, NATURE-IDENTI\nARTIFICIAL (COLA) FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)..\nNUTRITION INFORMATION (APPROXIMATE VALUES)\nSERVING-200 ml: 1.5 SERVINGS IN THIS PACK\nPER 100ml\n%RDA*\nPER SERVE\n39 kcal\n3.9%\nENERGY\nCARBOHYDRATE\n9.7 g\nTOTAL SUGARS\n9.5g\nB\n-ADDED SUGARS\n9.5 g\n38%\nTOTAL FAT\n09\n0%\n4\nPROTEIN\nOg\nSODIUM\n22 mg\n2.2%\nMANUFACTURED BY\nCHINDUSTAN COOL', '{\"overall_score\": 58, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product contains several ingredients that may warrant consideration for an adult with hormonal health conditions. High sugar content, caffeine, and artificial additives could potentially influence blood sugar regulation, sleep patterns, and overall metabolic balance in some individuals. Occasional consumption might be acceptable, but regular intake could be less ideal.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 4, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"CARBONATED WATER\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered safe and does not appear to pose specific concerns for hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SUGAR\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High intake of added sugars may potentially influence blood sugar regulation and could possibly impact hormonal balance in some individuals. The product contains 9.5g of added sugar per 100ml.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"ACIDITY REGULATOR (338) (Phosphoric Acid)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While generally recognized as safe in moderation, some research suggests a potential association between high intake of phosphoric acid and certain health outcomes, though direct impacts on hormonal health are not definitively established.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"CAFFEINE (8.1mg/100g)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caffeine intake, even in moderate amounts, could potentially influence sleep patterns and stress responses, which might in turn have an indirect effect on hormonal regulation in some individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SWEETENER\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Some studies suggest that certain artificial sweeteners might potentially affect gut microbiome balance or have metabolic effects, which could indirectly relate to hormonal health in some individuals, though more research is needed to establish definitive links.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"COLOUR (150d) (Caramel Colour IV)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caramel Colour IV may contain a byproduct called 4-methylimidazole (4-MeI), which some studies have linked to potential health concerns, though the impact on hormonal health is not well-established. It is generally considered an artificial additive.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FLAVOURS (NATURAL, NATURE-IDENTI ARTIFICIAL (COLA) FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"The inclusion of artificial flavoring substances might contribute to the overall additive load of the product, and some individuals may choose to limit consumption of artificial ingredients for general wellness purposes.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Content\", \"description\": \"This beverage contains a significant amount of added sugar (9.5g per 100ml, equating to 19g per 200ml serving). High intake of added sugars could potentially lead to rapid spikes in blood sugar, which may influence insulin sensitivity and could possibly affect hormonal balance over time, particularly for individuals with existing hormonal conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Artificial Additives\", \"description\": \"The product includes an acidity regulator (338), an artificial sweetener, a specific caramel color (150d), and artificial flavoring substances. Regular consumption of multiple artificial additives might be a concern for some individuals, as their long-term effects on general health and metabolism, including potential indirect impacts on hormonal regulation, are still areas of ongoing research.\"}, {\"title\": \"Caffeine Considerations\", \"description\": \"With 8.1mg of caffeine per 100ml, a 200ml serving would contain 16.2mg. While this is a moderate amount, caffeine intake could potentially affect sleep quality and stress hormone levels in sensitive individuals, which might indirectly influence overall hormonal health. It may be wise to be mindful of total daily caffeine intake.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Contribution\", \"description\": \"This product appears to offer minimal nutritional value beyond energy from sugars. It largely consists of \'empty calories,\' meaning it provides energy without significant amounts of vitamins, minerals, or fiber. For optimal health and hormonal balance, a diet rich in nutrient-dense foods is generally recommended, and beverages like this may not contribute positively to that goal.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consider limiting your intake of this beverage, especially if you are focusing on supporting hormonal balance, due to its sugar content and artificial additives.\", \"You may want to explore alternatives like plain water, herbal teas, or naturally flavored sparkling water, which generally do not contain added sugars or artificial ingredients.\", \"If consumed, perhaps aim for smaller portions or less frequent consumption to help manage your overall intake of sugar and additives.\", \"Be mindful of your total daily caffeine intake from all sources, as excessive caffeine could potentially influence sleep and stress, which might indirectly affect hormonal regulation.\", \"Consider consulting with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian for personalized dietary advice tailored to your specific hormonal health needs.\"]}', '2026-03-18 08:27:11'),
(28, 8, 'Gluco BISCUITS', 'Parle-G', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_687c107cdd8346a9a28602b723fe87bc.jpg', 'Parle-G\' Gluco BISCUITS\nINGREDIENTS: REFINED WHEAT FLOUR (MAIDA) (68%),\nSUGAR, REFINED PALM OIL, INVERT SUGAR SYRUP\n[SUGAR, CITRIC ACID], IODISED SALT, RAISING AGENTS\n[503 (ii), 500 (i)], MILK SOLIDS, FLOUR TREATMENT AGENT\n[1101 (i)] AND EMULSIFIER OF VEGETABLE ORIGIN [472e]\nCONTAINS ADDED FLAVOUR (ARTIFICIAL FLAVOURING\nSUBSTANCES-VANILLA\n(D-GLUCOSE, LEVULOSE)\nCONTAINS: WHEAT, MILK\nLOONSUMER CARE', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product contains a significant proportion of refined carbohydrates and multiple sources of added sugars, which may contribute to blood sugar fluctuations. For individuals focusing on hormonal health, a diet rich in highly processed ingredients, refined sugars, and certain fats could be a consideration. While it may be consumed in moderation, it might not be an ideal staple for a supportive dietary pattern.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 5, \"allergens_found\": [\"Wheat\", \"Milk\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"REFINED WHEAT FLOUR (MAIDA)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Refined grains, which make up a significant portion of this product, may contribute to rapid blood sugar fluctuations. Some dietary patterns rich in refined carbohydrates have been associated with potential impacts on hormonal balance for certain individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SUGAR\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"High intake of added sugars is generally associated with potential blood sugar imbalances and inflammation, which could potentially affect hormonal regulation for some individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"REFINED PALM OIL\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Refined palm oil is a source of saturated fat and has undergone processing. Diets high in certain types of fats may be a consideration for overall health and could potentially influence metabolic and hormonal pathways in some contexts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"INVERT SUGAR SYRUP\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is another form of added sugar, which, when consumed in excess, could potentially contribute to similar concerns regarding blood sugar and hormonal balance as regular sugar.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"IODISED SALT\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Iodised salt provides iodine, an essential nutrient, and in moderate amounts, it is generally considered safe for most adults.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"RAISING AGENTS [503 (ii), 500 (i)]\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are common leavening agents generally recognized as safe for consumption in the amounts typically found in baked goods.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"MILK SOLIDS\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While the user has no stated dairy allergy, milk solids are a processed dairy ingredient. For some individuals, certain dairy components might be considered in relation to hormonal balance, though this is not a universal effect.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FLOUR TREATMENT AGENT [1101 (i)]\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"This is an enzyme commonly used in baking to improve dough quality. It is generally considered safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"EMULSIFIER OF VEGETABLE ORIGIN [472e]\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Emulsifiers are food additives used for texture. Some processed food additives could be a consideration for individuals aiming for a less processed diet.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"ARTIFICIAL FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES-VANILLA\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Artificial flavorings are synthetic compounds. Some individuals may prefer to limit their intake of artificial additives as part of a generally less processed eating pattern.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"D-GLUCOSE\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"D-Glucose is a simple sugar that contributes to the overall sugar content of the product, which could potentially contribute to blood sugar fluctuations when consumed in higher amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"LEVULOSE\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Levulose is fructose, another simple sugar. High intake of sugars like fructose is often linked to potential metabolic considerations, which could indirectly relate to hormonal health for some individuals.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"This product contains multiple sources of added sugars\\u2014SUGAR, INVERT SUGAR SYRUP, D-GLUCOSE, and LEVULOSE\\u2014all listed high on the ingredient list. A higher intake of such sugars may contribute to blood sugar imbalances, which could potentially impact hormonal regulation for certain individuals.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The ingredients indicate a highly processed food, with refined wheat flour as the primary component, along with refined palm oil and several food additives. Diets consisting largely of highly processed foods are sometimes considered for their potential impact on overall health and well-being.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product includes several food additives, such as raising agents, a flour treatment agent, an emulsifier, and artificial flavouring. While many of these are generally recognized as safe, individuals aiming for a less processed or \'cleaner\' diet might prefer to limit the consumption of products with multiple additives.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Considerations\", \"description\": \"Due to the high proportion of refined ingredients and added sugars, this product may offer limited amounts of dietary fiber and essential micronutrients. A dietary pattern emphasizing whole, unprocessed foods is generally considered more supportive for overall health, including aspects related to hormonal balance.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consider consuming these biscuits infrequently and in small portions to help manage overall sugar and refined carbohydrate intake.\", \"You may want to explore snack options that are lower in refined sugars and higher in fiber and healthy fats, which could be more supportive for hormonal balance.\", \"Hydration is generally important; consider pairing such snacks with water or unsweetened beverages.\", \"Always consider a balanced dietary pattern that emphasizes whole foods, fruits, vegetables, and lean proteins for overall well-being, including hormonal health.\"]}', '2026-03-18 09:02:54'),
(29, 8, 'Biscuits', 'BRITANNIA', 65, 'MODERATE', '8_2ff7f43d32b34c7ead0fbb41e4aa51d5.jpg', 'h\nBRITANNIA\nIngredients\nREFINED WHEAT FLOUR (MAIDA) (73%), SUGAR, REFINED PALM OIL INVERT\nSUGAR SYRUP, MEK SOLIDS, RAISING AGENTS [503(11) & 500 (1)].\nIODIZED SALT, EMULSIFIER (4726), CALCIUM SALT, DOUGH\nCONDITIONER (223), VITAMINS, FERROUS SALT AND POTASSIUM IODATE.\nCONTAINS PERMITTED NATURAL COLOUR (1500) AND ADDED\nFLAVOURS NATURE IDENTICAL & ARTIFICIAL (MILK & VANILLA)\nFLAVOURING SUBSTANCES) (Numbers in brackets as per international\nNumbering System) CONTAINS WHEAT, MILK AND SULPHITE.', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product contains several refined ingredients and added sugars, which could potentially lead to fluctuations in blood sugar. While not inherently harmful, a high intake of such ingredients may be a consideration for individuals aiming to support hormonal balance. It also includes a number of food additives.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 6, \"allergens_found\": [\"Wheat\", \"Milk\", \"Sulphite\"], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"REFINED WHEAT FLOUR (MAIDA)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"As a refined carbohydrate, it could potentially lead to rapid blood sugar fluctuations. Maintaining stable blood sugar levels is often considered important for supporting hormonal balance.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SUGAR\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is a source of added sugars, which may contribute to blood sugar spikes. Sustained high sugar intake might be a consideration for metabolic health and could potentially influence hormonal regulation over time.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"REFINED PALM OIL\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Contains saturated fats. Some dietary patterns high in certain types of fats are sometimes linked to metabolic considerations, which could indirectly relate to hormonal health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"INVERT SUGAR SYRUP\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Another form of concentrated sugar, sharing similar considerations regarding blood sugar impact as regular sugar.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"MILK SOLIDS\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"For this user profile with no specified dairy allergy, milk solids are generally considered acceptable. The product label indicates \'MILK\' as an allergen, which is noted separately.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"RAISING AGENTS [503(ii) & 500(ii)]\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are common food additives generally considered safe when consumed in typical food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"IODIZED SALT\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Provides essential iodine, which is important for thyroid function. Sodium content might be a general dietary consideration, but in moderation, it is usually acceptable.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"EMULSIFIER (472e)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A common food emulsifier generally regarded as safe for consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"CALCIUM SALT\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"A source of calcium, often used for fortification. Generally considered safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"DOUGH CONDITIONER (223)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This is sodium metabisulphite, a sulphite. While generally safe for most, some individuals may experience sensitivities, and it contributes to the overall additive load. The label notes \'SULPHITE\' as an allergen.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"VITAMINS\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Fortification with vitamins is generally considered beneficial for nutritional intake.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FERROUS SALT\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Iron fortification, generally considered safe and beneficial for iron intake.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"POTASSIUM IODATE\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Another source of iodine fortification, generally considered safe.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"PERMITTED NATURAL COLOUR (150c)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While referred to as \'natural,\' some types of caramel colouring have been a subject of discussion regarding potential byproducts. It contributes to the overall additive load.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"ADDED FLAVOURS (NATURE IDENTICAL & ARTIFICIAL (MILK & VANILLA) FLAVOURING SUBSTANCES)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Contains artificial flavors. Some individuals may prefer to limit consumption of artificial ingredients as part of a whole-foods approach to health.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"This product contains significant amounts of added sugars, including sugar and invert sugar syrup, which are high on the ingredient list. High intake of such ingredients could potentially contribute to fluctuations in blood sugar, which may be a consideration for maintaining hormonal balance.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"The product appears to be highly processed, featuring refined wheat flour as the primary ingredient, along with refined oils and numerous additives. Highly processed foods might offer less nutritional density compared to whole, unprocessed alternatives, which could be a factor for overall health and hormonal well-being.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The product includes several food additives, such as raising agents, an emulsifier, a sulphite dough conditioner (223), a caramel colour (150c), and artificial flavors. While many of these are approved for use, some individuals may prefer to limit their intake of products with a higher additive load, especially when managing specific health conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Value\", \"description\": \"Primarily composed of refined carbohydrates and sugars, this product may not provide optimal micronutrient support. For individuals focused on hormonal health, a dietary pattern rich in whole foods, fiber, and diverse nutrients is often considered more beneficial.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consider moderating your intake of this product due to its refined ingredients and high sugar content, which may influence blood sugar stability.\", \"You may want to prioritize a diet rich in whole, unprocessed foods, lean proteins, healthy fats, and ample fiber to better support hormonal health.\", \"Ensure adequate hydration and balance any consumption of this product with nutrient-dense options to maintain overall well-being.\", \"If you have specific concerns about sulphites or any other ingredient in relation to your hormonal conditions, consulting a healthcare professional or registered dietitian could be beneficial.\"]}', '2026-03-18 09:03:18'),
