(35, 6, 'Pepsi-Cola', 'Pepsi', 35, 'HIGH', '6_1710e78d6364438b8597a8aee679a390.jpg', 'COLA FLAVOURED SOFT DRINK\nIngredients: Carbonated Water, Sugar,\nCaramel Colour (E150d), Phosphoric Acid,\nCaffeine, Natural Flavourings. Bottled by\nSimonds Farsons Cisk Plc, The Brewery,\nMdina road, Mriehel, Malta, BKR3000,\nunder authority of PepsiCo, Inc., N.Y., USA.\nMalta freephone 8007 4403. For best before\ndate-see neck of bottle. PEPSI, PEPSI-COLA\nand the Pepsi Globe are registered trademarks\nof PepsiCo, Inc. Store in a cool, dry place\nand protect from heat and sunlight\nPEPSI-CLA\nwww.p', '{\"overall_score\": 35, \"risk_level\": \"HIGH\", \"overview\": \"This cola-flavoured soft drink contains a notable amount of sugar, caffeine, and certain additives, which could potentially be a concern for individuals managing blood sugar levels and cardiovascular health. It might not be the most ideal beverage choice for a senior with these specific health conditions.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Carbonated Water\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered to be a relatively neutral ingredient that may not pose specific concerns for individuals managing blood sugar or cardiovascular conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"AVOID\", \"reason\": \"The significant sugar content could potentially make it challenging to maintain stable blood sugar levels and might not align with dietary recommendations for cardiovascular health management.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caramel Colour (E150d)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Some studies have explored potential concerns regarding certain caramel colours, including E150d, which might be a consideration for sensitive individuals or those with existing health conditions. Its presence might warrant a cautious approach to frequent consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Phosphoric Acid\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Regular consumption of beverages containing phosphoric acid might potentially have implications for bone mineral density over an extended period, which could be a consideration for seniors. It might also potentially contribute to dental enamel erosion.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Caffeine\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Caffeine could potentially influence blood pressure and heart rate in some individuals, which may be a factor to consider for those managing cardiovascular conditions. It might also have varying effects on blood sugar regulation.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Natural Flavourings\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These ingredients are typically present in small amounts and are generally considered to be of low concern for most individuals, potentially not posing specific risks for blood sugar or cardiovascular health.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar Analysis\", \"description\": \"The high sugar content in this product could potentially contribute to difficulties in maintaining stable blood sugar levels and might be a consideration for those managing diabetes or aiming to support cardiovascular wellness.\"}, {\"title\": \"Additive Load\", \"description\": \"The presence of caramel colour (E150d) and phosphoric acid might be a factor to consider, as some individuals prefer to limit the intake of such additives, particularly with frequent consumption. Their long-term effects for sensitive populations are sometimes discussed.\"}, {\"title\": \"Caffeine Considerations\", \"description\": \"The caffeine content could potentially influence the cardiovascular system, possibly affecting heart rate or blood pressure in some sensitive individuals, which may be a point of consideration for someone with existing cardiovascular conditions.\"}, {\"title\": \"Acidity Concerns\", \"description\": \"The phosphoric acid could potentially contribute to increased acidity, which some evidence suggests might have implications for dental health and, in some contexts, bone health over very long periods, particularly in older individuals.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"You may want to consider opting for unsweetened beverages, such as water or plain herbal teas, as more hydration-friendly alternatives.\", \"It could be beneficial to monitor your intake of products containing significant amounts of sugar and caffeine, especially given your health profile.\", \"Discussing specific dietary choices, like regular consumption of soft drinks, with your healthcare provider could provide personalized advice relevant to your blood sugar and cardiovascular management.\", \"Exploring naturally flavoured waters or sparkling water with a squeeze of lemon or lime might offer a refreshing option with fewer potential concerns.\"]}', '2026-03-24 03:15:32'),
(36, 6, 'American Style Cream & Onion Potato Chips', '', 45, 'MODERATE', '6_3807a3fccda3486ea32161a8b9f9061a.jpg', 'American Style\nCream & Onion\nIngredients\nPotato, Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Sunflower Oil),\n*Seasoning (Sugar, lodised Salt, Milk Solids, Spices &\nCondiments, Maltodextrin, Flavour (Natural & Nature Identical\nFlavouring Substances), Cheese Powder, Hydrolysed Vegetable\nProtein, Flavour Enhancers (627, 631), Edible Vegetable Oil (Palm,\nCoconut), Anticaking Agent (551)).\n*As flavoring agent. Contains Onion\nAllergen Advice: Contains Soy, Milk, May Contain Sulphite\nfssai\nLic No. 10014054000435\nINGREDIENTS AND NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION MAY VARY BASED ON CURRENT\nRUNNING PRODUCT FORMULATION AND STOCK AVAILABILITY FOR YOUR LOCATION\nPLEASE REFER TO THE PRODUCT LABEL FOR DETAILS', '{\"overall_score\": 45, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product, an American Style Cream & Onion snack, appears to be a highly processed food item. It contains several ingredients that could potentially be a consideration for a senior user managing blood sugar and cardiovascular health, such as added sugars, higher sodium content, and saturated fats. While it may offer taste, its overall nutritional profile might not be ideal for frequent consumption given the user\'s health profile.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"High\", \"additives_count\": 3, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Potato\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"As a fried chip, potatoes become a source of rapidly digestible carbohydrates, which could potentially influence blood sugar levels, particularly for individuals managing blood sugar.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palmolein, Sunflower Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palmolein may contain a notable amount of saturated fat, which might be a consideration for individuals with cardiovascular concerns. Sunflower oil, while generally polyunsaturated, is often highly processed.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Sugar is a direct carbohydrate source that could contribute to fluctuations in blood sugar levels, which may be a concern for those managing blood sugar.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This product may contain a considerable amount of sodium from salt, which could potentially influence blood pressure and might be a consideration for individuals with cardiovascular health concerns.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Milk Solids\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Milk solids are a dairy derivative; as no specific dairy allergy or sensitivity is noted for this user, they are generally considered safe in this context, although they may contribute to the overall fat content.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are generally considered safe ingredients and may contribute flavor without direct health concerns for this profile.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Maltodextrin\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Maltodextrin is a highly processed carbohydrate that may have a high glycemic index, which could potentially affect blood sugar levels for individuals with blood sugar management needs.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural & Nature Identical Flavouring Substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"\'Nature identical\' flavors are often synthetic and can contribute to the highly processed nature of the food, which might not be ideal for a health-conscious diet.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Cheese Powder\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Cheese powder is a processed ingredient that could contribute to overall sodium and fat content, which may be a consideration for cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Hydrolysed Vegetable Protein\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Hydrolysed vegetable protein is a processed ingredient that may contain naturally occurring glutamates, which some individuals might prefer to limit as part of a highly processed food item. It could also be derived from soy, a common allergen.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour Enhancers (627, 631)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are food additives that can contribute to the ultra-processed nature of the snack, which may not align with dietary recommendations for individuals managing health conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Edible Vegetable Oil (Palm, Coconut)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palm and coconut oils are known to contain higher levels of saturated fats, which could be a consideration for individuals focusing on cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Anticaking Agent (551)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Silicon dioxide is generally recognized as safe for consumption in small amounts and is unlikely to pose a direct health concern for this user profile.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Blood Sugar Management Considerations\", \"description\": \"This product contains ingredients such as potato (in fried form), added sugar, and maltodextrin. These components are sources of carbohydrates that could potentially lead to fluctuations in blood sugar levels. For a senior individual managing blood sugar, consuming such items in moderation or being mindful of portion sizes may be prudent, as they might influence glycemic control.\"}, {\"title\": \"Cardiovascular Health Considerations\", \"description\": \"Several ingredients in this snack, including palmolein, palm oil, coconut oil, and iodised salt, could be a concern for cardiovascular health. Palmolein, palm, and coconut oils may contribute to the intake of saturated fats, which some dietary guidelines suggest limiting for cardiovascular well-being. Additionally, the presence of iodised salt indicates potential for higher sodium content, which could play a role in blood pressure management for individuals with cardiovascular concerns.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level and Additive Load\", \"description\": \"This snack appears to be a highly processed food item, indicated by multiple forms of processed oils, various flavourings (\'natural & nature identical\'), hydrolysed vegetable protein, cheese powder, and specific flavour enhancers (627, 631). Consuming ultra-processed foods frequently may not align with dietary patterns often recommended for overall health and managing chronic conditions in seniors.\"}, {\"title\": \"Potential Allergen Presence\", \"description\": \"While the user has not specified any known allergies or sensitivities, the product label explicitly states \'Contains Soy, Milk, May Contain Sulphite\'. Individuals with sensitivities to these ingredients would generally need to exercise caution. For this user, given no known sensitivities, this information serves as a general awareness note about the product\'s composition.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"You may want to consider consuming this product in very small, infrequent portions, especially if you are actively managing blood sugar and cardiovascular health.\", \"It could be helpful to monitor your blood sugar response after consuming such snacks to understand how they might affect your individual glycemic levels.\", \"You might consider opting for less processed snack alternatives that are lower in added sugars, sodium, and saturated fats, and higher in fiber and whole ingredients.\", \"It could be beneficial to consult with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian to discuss suitable snack options that align with your specific health management goals.\"]}', '2026-03-24 11:06:23'),
(37, 6, 'Enhanced Purified Water', 'Member\'s Mark', 65, 'MODERATE', '6_25db86cbf9a149c68f0d26f62aabb7c5.jpg', 'USED BY\nSBRY\'S\nPED WATER\nLENHANCED\nFOR TASTE\n1237 mL)\nINGREDIENTS: PURIFIED WATER, CALCIUM\nCHLORIDE, SODIUM BICARBONATE\nDISTRIBUTED BY SAM\'S WEST, INC.\nBENTONVILLE, AR 72716\nPURIFIED BY REVERSE OSMOSIS\nNO BPA ADDED\nWARNING: Cap is a small part and poses a\nCHOKING HAZARD, particularly for children.\nWe would love to hear\nMember\'s Mark experien\nsamsclub.com member\nFOR A REPORT ON WATER\nINFORMATION\nwww.AGABAMA.CO\n\"RECYCLABLE BOTTLE A\nEMPTY BOTTLE AND P', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product consists of purified water enhanced with calcium chloride and sodium bicarbonate. For a senior user with cardiovascular and blood sugar concerns, the presence of sodium from sodium bicarbonate could potentially be a consideration for overall sodium intake, which is often linked to blood pressure management. While generally hydrating, individuals may want to consider their total intake of mineral additives.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Nil\", \"additives_count\": 2, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"PURIFIED WATER\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Purified water is generally considered safe for consumption and provides essential hydration, which is important for overall bodily functions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"CALCIUM CHLORIDE\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While a source of calcium and often used to enhance taste, some studies suggest that very high calcium intake, particularly from certain sources, might be a factor for cardiovascular health in specific individuals. In the small amounts found in water, it is generally considered safe, but individuals with cardiovascular conditions may want to consider their overall calcium consumption.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SODIUM BICARBONATE\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"This ingredient contains sodium. A higher intake of sodium is often linked to blood pressure concerns, which could be a consideration for individuals managing cardiovascular conditions. People monitoring their blood sugar and cardiovascular health may want to be mindful of their total sodium consumption from all dietary sources.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sodium Content Analysis\", \"description\": \"The presence of sodium bicarbonate introduces a small amount of sodium to the water. For individuals with cardiovascular conditions, monitoring overall sodium intake is often recommended, as higher sodium levels are often associated with blood pressure concerns. While the amount in water is likely minimal, consistent consumption could potentially contribute to daily sodium totals.\"}, {\"title\": \"Mineral Additive Considerations\", \"description\": \"The water is enhanced with calcium chloride. While calcium is an essential mineral, excessive intake from all sources might be a consideration for certain individuals with cardiovascular health concerns. These mineral additives are generally safe in the small quantities found in enhanced water, but it is often wise to consider the cumulative intake from all dietary sources.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level\", \"description\": \"Purified water, especially through reverse osmosis as indicated, is a processed product. While this process effectively removes impurities, it also removes natural minerals. The subsequent addition of calcium chloride and sodium bicarbonate is intended to reintroduce some minerals and enhance taste, making it a moderately processed beverage.\"}, {\"title\": \"Hydration Benefits\", \"description\": \"Despite the presence of mineral additives, the primary benefit of this product is hydration, which is crucial for maintaining bodily functions, regulating body temperature, and supporting overall health for individuals of all ages, including seniors. Adequate hydration may indirectly support cardiovascular health and overall well-being.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"You may want to consider monitoring your overall daily sodium intake from all food and beverage sources, especially if you are managing cardiovascular health.\", \"It might be beneficial to discuss the suitability of enhanced waters, particularly regarding mineral additives, with your healthcare provider or a registered dietitian.\", \"For primary hydration, you could consider alternating between enhanced water and plain, unadulterated water to vary your mineral intake.\", \"Observe how your body responds to regular consumption of this enhanced water, particularly concerning any cardiovascular or blood pressure indicators you monitor.\"]}', '2026-03-25 06:20:51'),
(38, 6, 'Chilli Chatka Flavour Snack', 'Kurkure', 55, 'MODERATE', '6_8caf87c2be074a3ca9afd9d62c5143bc.jpg', 'Kurkure\nINGREDIENTS\nCHILLI CHATKA FLAVOUR\nCEREAL PRODUCTS (57%) (RICE MEAL (38%), CORN MEAL\n(19%)), EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL (PALMOLEIN),\n*SEASONING (-SPICES & CONDIMENTS, SUGAR, IODISED\nSALT, ACIDITY REGULATORS (330, 296), FLAVOUR\n(NATURAL AND NATURE IDENTICAL FLAVOURING\nSUBSRANCES), FLAVOUR ENHANCERS (627, 631), EDIBLE\nVEGETABLE OIL (CORN OIL), COLOR (160C), EMULSIFIER\n(414)), GRAM MEAL (6%).\n*AS FLAVOURING AGENT.\n~CONTAINS ONION AND GARLIC.', '{\"overall_score\": 55, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product contains several ingredients that could potentially be a consideration for a senior user managing blood sugar and cardiovascular conditions. It includes refined grains, added sugar, sodium, and certain types of fats, which may warrant mindful consumption. The presence of multiple additives also suggests a more processed food item.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Medium\", \"additives_count\": 7, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"CEREAL PRODUCTS (RICE MEAL, CORN MEAL)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are refined grain products, which could potentially be rapidly digested and might influence blood sugar levels, which could be a consideration for individuals with blood sugar conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL (PALMOLEIN)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palmolein is a fractionated palm oil that may contain a relatively higher proportion of saturated fats compared to some other vegetable oils, which could potentially be a factor for cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SPICES & CONDIMENTS\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These ingredients are generally considered acceptable and may offer some beneficial compounds, typically without specific concerns for the user\'s health profile.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"SUGAR\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Added sugar could potentially contribute to fluctuations in blood sugar levels, which may be a concern for individuals managing blood sugar conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"IODISED SALT\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Sodium intake is often considered a factor in managing blood pressure, which could be relevant for cardiovascular health. Moderation might be suggested.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"ACIDITY REGULATORS (330, 296)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"These are generally recognized as safe food additives and are not typically associated with adverse effects for the user\'s health profile when consumed in typical food amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FLAVOUR (NATURAL AND NATURE IDENTICAL FLAVOURING SUBSRANCES)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While often considered safe, \'nature identical\' indicates synthetic components, and some individuals might have sensitivities to certain flavouring agents, potentially contributing to the overall additive load.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"FLAVOUR ENHANCERS (627, 631)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are common food additives used to intensify savory flavors. While generally recognized as safe, some individuals might experience sensitivities, and they contribute to the overall processed nature of the product.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL (CORN OIL)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Corn oil is generally higher in omega-6 fatty acids, and an imbalance in omega-6 to omega-3 ratios in the diet is sometimes suggested as a potential factor in inflammation, which could be a consideration for cardiovascular well-being.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"COLOR (160C)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Paprika extract is a natural colorant, and is not typically associated with specific health concerns for the user\'s profile.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"EMULSIFIER (414)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Acacia gum is a natural gum often used as an emulsifier and thickener, generally considered safe for consumption without specific concerns for the user\'s health profile.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"GRAM MEAL (CHICKPEA FLOUR)\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Gram meal is a legume-based ingredient that may provide some dietary fiber, which could be beneficial for digestion and might help in moderating blood sugar responses.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Sugar and Carbohydrate Analysis\", \"description\": \"The product lists \'sugar\' as an ingredient and contains refined cereal products like rice meal and corn meal. These ingredients could potentially contribute to a quicker rise in blood sugar levels, which may be a consideration for individuals managing blood sugar conditions. Monitoring overall carbohydrate intake might be suggested.\"}, {\"title\": \"Cardiovascular Considerations\", \"description\": \"This product includes palmolein, which may contain saturated fats, and corn oil, which is typically higher in omega-6 fatty acids. High sodium from \'iodised salt\' is also present. These components, particularly when consumed in larger quantities, could potentially be factors for individuals focused on supporting cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Processing Level and Additive Load\", \"description\": \"With multiple refined ingredients, flavorings, flavor enhancers (627, 631), and acidity regulators, this product appears to be quite processed. The presence of several additives might contribute to a higher overall additive load, which some individuals may choose to limit in their diet.\"}, {\"title\": \"Nutritional Balance\", \"description\": \"While gram meal offers some fiber, the overall nutritional profile of this snack, primarily composed of refined grains, oils, sugar, and salt, may not contribute significantly to a balanced diet. It might be considered a treat rather than a primary nutritional source for those with specific health conditions.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"You may want to consider consuming this product in moderation to help manage intake of refined carbohydrates, sugar, sodium, and certain fats.\", \"It could be beneficial to compare this product with other snack options that may offer lower sugar, sodium, and saturated fat content, or higher fiber.\", \"Balancing such snacks with a diet rich in whole, unprocessed foods like fruits, vegetables, and lean proteins may contribute to overall well-being.\", \"If you have specific dietary concerns related to your blood sugar or cardiovascular conditions, discussing your snack choices with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian might provide personalized guidance.\"]}', '2026-03-25 06:22:42'),
(40, 6, 'CHILLI CHATKA FLAVOUR', 'Kurkure', 65, 'MODERATE', '6_099d6c8ba9e24c38bde7c048fd60e7f7.jpg', 'Kurkure\nINGREDIENTS\nCHILLI CHATKA FLAVOUR\nCEREAL PRODUCTS (57%) (RICE MEAL (38%), CORN MEAL\n(19%)), EDIBLE VEGETABLE OIL (PALMOLEIN),\n*SEASONING (-SPICES & CONDIMENTS, SUGAR, IODISED\nSALT, ACIDITY REGULATORS (330, 296), FLAVOUR\n(NATURAL AND NATURE IDENTICAL FLAVOURING\nSUBSRANCES), FLAVOUR ENHANCERS (627, 631), EDIBLE\nVEGETABLE OIL (CORN OIL), COLOR (160C), EMULSIFIER\n(414)), GRAM MEAL (6%).\n*AS FLAVOURING AGENT.\n~CONTAINS ONION AND GARLIC.', '{\"overall_score\": 65, \"risk_level\": \"MODERATE\", \"overview\": \"This product is a highly processed snack containing refined carbohydrates, added sugar, and sodium, which could be a consideration for individuals managing blood sugar and cardiovascular health. It also includes several food additives and refined vegetable oils. While no dairy ingredients are explicitly listed, individuals with a dairy allergy might want to remain cautious about potential cross-contamination.\", \"sugar_estimate\": \"Medium\", \"additives_count\": 6, \"allergens_found\": [], \"ingredients\": [{\"ingredient_name\": \"Cereal Products (Rice Meal, Corn Meal)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"These are refined carbohydrates which could potentially affect blood sugar levels, which might be a consideration for individuals managing blood sugar conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Palmolein (Edible Vegetable Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Palmolein is a refined vegetable oil, and some sources suggest that processed oils might be a consideration for individuals with cardiovascular concerns if consumed frequently or in larger amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Spices & Condiments\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Generally considered safe, though individual sensitivities to specific spices (like onion and garlic noted here) can vary. These are typically consumed in small amounts.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Sugar\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Added sugar could potentially contribute to fluctuations in blood sugar levels, which may be a consideration for individuals managing blood sugar conditions.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Iodised Salt\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While iodine is essential, excessive sodium intake, which can come from salt, might be a factor for individuals monitoring their cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Acidity Regulators (330, 296)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Citric acid (330) and Malic acid (296) are generally recognized as safe, but as additives, they could be part of an overall assessment of processed food intake for some individuals.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour (Natural and Nature Identical Flavouring Substances)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"While \'natural\' implies derivation from natural sources, \'nature identical\' indicates synthetic production. Some individuals might prefer to limit intake of complex or synthetic flavorings.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Flavour Enhancers (627, 631)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Disodium Guanylate (627) and Disodium Inosinate (631) are purine-based flavor enhancers often found in ultra-processed foods. Some individuals might experience sensitivities to these additives.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Corn Oil (Edible Vegetable Oil)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Corn oil is a refined vegetable oil high in omega-6 fatty acids. An imbalance of omega-6 to omega-3 fatty acids might be a consideration for individuals managing cardiovascular health.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Color (160C)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Paprika extract (160C) is a natural colorant, but it is still an additive. Some individuals might experience sensitivities to food colorings, contributing to the overall additive load.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Emulsifier (414)\", \"status\": \"CAUTION\", \"reason\": \"Acacia Gum (414) is generally considered safe but is an additive. For individuals preferring to minimize processed ingredients, its presence might be noted.\"}, {\"ingredient_name\": \"Gram Meal\", \"status\": \"SAFE\", \"reason\": \"Gram meal (chickpea flour) is a legume flour, which can contribute some protein and fiber. It is generally considered suitable for most individuals.\"}], \"risk_analysis\": [{\"title\": \"Processing Level & Additive Load\", \"description\": \"This product appears to be a highly processed snack, primarily made from refined cereal products and contains several additives including acidity regulators, flavor enhancers (627, 631), a color (160C), and an emulsifier (414). Frequent consumption of highly processed foods with a significant additive load might be a consideration for general health.\"}, {\"title\": \"Macronutrient Composition\", \"description\": \"The main ingredients include refined cereal products (rice and corn meal) and refined edible vegetable oils (palmolein, corn oil). A diet high in refined carbohydrates might potentially contribute to fluctuations in blood sugar, while an intake of certain processed fats could be a factor for cardiovascular health, especially if consumed regularly.\"}, {\"title\": \"Allergen Check\", \"description\": \"The user has a dairy allergy. Based on the provided ingredients list, no dairy ingredients appear to be explicitly listed. However, cross-contamination in manufacturing facilities is always a possibility for highly sensitive individuals, which is not usually stated on ingredient labels unless specifically certified.\"}], \"guidance\": [\"Consider consuming this product in moderation due to the presence of refined carbohydrates, added sugar, and sodium, which might be a consideration for blood sugar and cardiovascular health.\", \"You may want to monitor your portion sizes to help manage your intake of calories, sugar, and sodium effectively.\", \"As the product contains multiple food additives, you might consider prioritizing whole, unprocessed foods more frequently for overall nutritional balance.\", \"Given the dairy allergy, while no dairy ingredients are explicitly listed, individuals with severe allergies might consider seeking clarification on potential cross-contamination if concerns persist.\", \"You may wish to balance snack choices with options that are richer in fiber, lean protein, and healthy fats, which could support blood sugar management and cardiovascular health.\"]}', '2026-03-28 03:44:40');
